2994 
2995 void OpenMPIRBuilder::createIfVersion(CanonicalLoopInfo *CanonicalLoop,
2996  Value *IfCond, ValueToValueMapTy &VMap,
2997  const Twine &NamePrefix) {
2998  Function *F = CanonicalLoop->getFunction();
2999 
3000  // Define where if branch should be inserted
3001  Instruction *SplitBefore;
3002  if (Instruction::classof(IfCond)) {
3003  SplitBefore = dyn_cast<Instruction>(IfCond);
3004  } else {
3005  SplitBefore = CanonicalLoop->getPreheader()->getTerminator();
3006  }
3007 
3008  // TODO: We should not rely on pass manager. Currently we use pass manager
3009  // only for getting llvm::Loop which corresponds to given CanonicalLoopInfo
3010  // object. We should have a method which returns all blocks between
3011  // CanonicalLoopInfo::getHeader() and CanonicalLoopInfo::getAfter()
3012  FunctionAnalysisManager FAM;
3013  FAM.registerPass([]() { return DominatorTreeAnalysis(); });
3014  FAM.registerPass([]() { return LoopAnalysis(); });
3015  FAM.registerPass([]() { return PassInstrumentationAnalysis(); });
3016 
3017  // Get the loop which needs to be cloned
3018  LoopAnalysis LIA;
3019  LoopInfo &&LI = LIA.run(*F, FAM);
3020  Loop *L = LI.getLoopFor(CanonicalLoop->getHeader());
3021 
3022  // Create additional blocks for the if statement
3023  BasicBlock *Head = SplitBefore->getParent();
3024  Instruction *HeadOldTerm = Head->getTerminator();
3025  llvm::LLVMContext &C = Head->getContext();
3026  llvm::BasicBlock *ThenBlock = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(
3027  C, NamePrefix + ".if.then", Head->getParent(), Head->getNextNode());
3028  llvm::BasicBlock *ElseBlock = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(
3029  C, NamePrefix + ".if.else", Head->getParent(), CanonicalLoop->getExit());
3030 
3031  // Create if condition branch.
3032  Builder.SetInsertPoint(HeadOldTerm);
3033  Instruction *BrInstr =
3034  Builder.CreateCondBr(IfCond, ThenBlock, /*ifFalse*/ ElseBlock);
3035  InsertPointTy IP{BrInstr->getParent(), ++BrInstr->getIterator()};
3036  // Then block contains branch to omp loop which needs to be vectorized
3037  spliceBB(IP, ThenBlock, false);
3038  ThenBlock->replaceSuccessorsPhiUsesWith(Head, ThenBlock);
3039 
3040  Builder.SetInsertPoint(ElseBlock);
3041 
3042  // Clone loop for the else branch
3043  SmallVector<BasicBlock *, 8> NewBlocks;
3044 
3045  VMap[CanonicalLoop->getPreheader()] = ElseBlock;
3046  for (BasicBlock *Block : L->getBlocks()) {
3047  BasicBlock *NewBB = CloneBasicBlock(Block, VMap, "", F);
3048  NewBB->moveBefore(CanonicalLoop->getExit());
3049  VMap[Block] = NewBB;
3050  NewBlocks.push_back(NewBB);
3051  }
3052  remapInstructionsInBlocks(NewBlocks, VMap);
3053  Builder.CreateBr(NewBlocks.front());
3054 }
3055 
3056 unsigned
3057 OpenMPIRBuilder::getOpenMPDefaultSimdAlign(const Triple &TargetTriple,
3058  const StringMap<bool> &Features) {
3059  if (TargetTriple.isX86()) {
3060  if (Features.lookup("avx512f"))
3061  return 512;
3062  else if (Features.lookup("avx"))
3063  return 256;
3064  return 128;
3065  }
3066  if (TargetTriple.isPPC())
3067  return 128;
3068  if (TargetTriple.isWasm())
3069  return 128;
3070  return 0;
3071 }
3072 
3073 void OpenMPIRBuilder::applySimd(CanonicalLoopInfo *CanonicalLoop,
3074  MapVector<Value *, Value *> AlignedVars,
3075  Value *IfCond, OrderKind Order,
3076  ConstantInt *Simdlen, ConstantInt *Safelen) {
3077  LLVMContext &Ctx = Builder.getContext();
3078 
3079  Function *F = CanonicalLoop->getFunction();
3080 
3081  // TODO: We should not rely on pass manager. Currently we use pass manager
3082  // only for getting llvm::Loop which corresponds to given CanonicalLoopInfo
3083  // object. We should have a method which returns all blocks between
3084  // CanonicalLoopInfo::getHeader() and CanonicalLoopInfo::getAfter()
3085  FunctionAnalysisManager FAM;
3086  FAM.registerPass([]() { return DominatorTreeAnalysis(); });
3087  FAM.registerPass([]() { return LoopAnalysis(); });
3088  FAM.registerPass([]() { return PassInstrumentationAnalysis(); });
3089 
3090  LoopAnalysis LIA;
3091  LoopInfo &&LI = LIA.run(*F, FAM);
3092 
3093  Loop *L = LI.getLoopFor(CanonicalLoop->getHeader());
3094  if (AlignedVars.size()) {
3095  InsertPointTy IP = Builder.saveIP();
3096  Builder.SetInsertPoint(CanonicalLoop->getPreheader()->getTerminator());
3097  for (auto &AlignedItem : AlignedVars) {
3098  Value *AlignedPtr = AlignedItem.first;
3099  Value *Alignment = AlignedItem.second;
3100  Builder.CreateAlignmentAssumption(F->getParent()->getDataLayout(),
3101  AlignedPtr, Alignment);
3102  }
3103  Builder.restoreIP(IP);
3104  }
3105 
3106  if (IfCond) {
3107  ValueToValueMapTy VMap;
3108  createIfVersion(CanonicalLoop, IfCond, VMap, "simd");
3109  // Add metadata to the cloned loop which disables vectorization
3110  Value *MappedLatch = VMap.lookup(CanonicalLoop->getLatch());
3111  assert(MappedLatch &&
3112  "Cannot find value which corresponds to original loop latch");
3113  assert(isa<BasicBlock>(MappedLatch) &&
3114  "Cannot cast mapped latch block value to BasicBlock");
3115  BasicBlock *NewLatchBlock = dyn_cast<BasicBlock>(MappedLatch);
3116  ConstantAsMetadata *BoolConst =
3117  ConstantAsMetadata::get(ConstantInt::getFalse(Type::getInt1Ty(Ctx)));
3118  addBasicBlockMetadata(
3119  NewLatchBlock,
3120  {MDNode::get(Ctx, {MDString::get(Ctx, "llvm.loop.vectorize.enable"),
3121  BoolConst})});
3122  }
3123 
3124  SmallSet<BasicBlock *, 8> Reachable;
3125 
3126  // Get the basic blocks from the loop in which memref instructions
3127  // can be found.
3128  // TODO: Generalize getting all blocks inside a CanonicalizeLoopInfo,
3129  // preferably without running any passes.
3130  for (BasicBlock *Block : L->getBlocks()) {
3131  if (Block == CanonicalLoop->getCond() ||
3132  Block == CanonicalLoop->getHeader())
3133  continue;
3134  Reachable.insert(Block);
3135  }
3136 
3137  SmallVector<Metadata *> LoopMDList;
3138 
3139  // In presence of finite 'safelen', it may be unsafe to mark all
3140  // the memory instructions parallel, because loop-carried
3141  // dependences of 'safelen' iterations are possible.
3142  // If clause order(concurrent) is specified then the memory instructions
3143  // are marked parallel even if 'safelen' is finite.
3144  if ((Safelen == nullptr) || (Order == OrderKind::OMP_ORDER_concurrent)) {
3145  // Add access group metadata to memory-access instructions.
3146  MDNode *AccessGroup = MDNode::getDistinct(Ctx, {});
3147  for (BasicBlock *BB : Reachable)
3148  addSimdMetadata(BB, AccessGroup, LI);
3149  // TODO: If the loop has existing parallel access metadata, have
3150  // to combine two lists.
3151  LoopMDList.push_back(MDNode::get(
3152  Ctx, {MDString::get(Ctx, "llvm.loop.parallel_accesses"), AccessGroup}));
3153  }
3154 
3155  // Use the above access group metadata to create loop level
3156  // metadata, which should be distinct for each loop.
3157  ConstantAsMetadata *BoolConst =
3158  ConstantAsMetadata::get(ConstantInt::getTrue(Type::getInt1Ty(Ctx)));
3159  LoopMDList.push_back(MDNode::get(
3160  Ctx, {MDString::get(Ctx, "llvm.loop.vectorize.enable"), BoolConst}));
3161 
3162  if (Simdlen || Safelen) {
3163  // If both simdlen and safelen clauses are specified, the value of the
3164  // simdlen parameter must be less than or equal to the value of the safelen
3165  // parameter. Therefore, use safelen only in the absence of simdlen.
3166  ConstantInt *VectorizeWidth = Simdlen == nullptr ? Safelen : Simdlen;
3167  LoopMDList.push_back(
3168  MDNode::get(Ctx, {MDString::get(Ctx, "llvm.loop.vectorize.width"),
3169  ConstantAsMetadata::get(VectorizeWidth)}));
3170  }
3171 
3172  addLoopMetadata(CanonicalLoop, LoopMDList);
3173 }
3174 
3175 /// Create the TargetMachine object to query the backend for optimization
3176 /// preferences.
3177 ///
3178 /// Ideally, this would be passed from the front-end to the OpenMPBuilder, but
3179 /// e.g. Clang does not pass it to its CodeGen layer and creates it only when
3180 /// needed for the LLVM pass pipline. We use some default options to avoid
3181 /// having to pass too many settings from the frontend that probably do not
3182 /// matter.
3183 ///
3184 /// Currently, TargetMachine is only used sometimes by the unrollLoopPartial
3185 /// method. If we are going to use TargetMachine for more purposes, especially
3186 /// those that are sensitive to TargetOptions, RelocModel and CodeModel, it
3187 /// might become be worth requiring front-ends to pass on their TargetMachine,
3188 /// or at least cache it between methods. Note that while fontends such as Clang
3189 /// have just a single main TargetMachine per translation unit, "target-cpu" and
3190 /// "target-features" that determine the TargetMachine are per-function and can
3191 /// be overrided using __attribute__((target("OPTIONS"))).
3192 static std::unique_ptr<TargetMachine>
3193 createTargetMachine(Function *F, CodeGenOpt::Level OptLevel) {
3194  Module *M = F->getParent();
3195 
3196  StringRef CPU = F->getFnAttribute("target-cpu").getValueAsString();
3197  StringRef Features = F->getFnAttribute("target-features").getValueAsString();
3198  const std::string &Triple = M->getTargetTriple();
3199 
3200  std::string Error;
3201  const llvm::Target *TheTarget = TargetRegistry::lookupTarget(Triple, Error);
3202  if (!TheTarget)
3203  return {};
3204 
3205  llvm::TargetOptions Options;
3206  return std::unique_ptr<TargetMachine>(TheTarget->createTargetMachine(
3207  Triple, CPU, Features, Options, /*RelocModel=*/std::nullopt,
3208  /*CodeModel=*/std::nullopt, OptLevel));
3209 }
3210 
3211 /// Heuristically determine the best-performant unroll factor for \p CLI. This
3212 /// depends on the target processor. We are re-using the same heuristics as the
3213 /// LoopUnrollPass.
3214 static int32_t computeHeuristicUnrollFactor(CanonicalLoopInfo *CLI) {
3215  Function *F = CLI->getFunction();
3216 
3217  // Assume the user requests the most aggressive unrolling, even if the rest of
3218  // the code is optimized using a lower setting.
3219  CodeGenOpt::Level OptLevel = CodeGenOpt::Aggressive;
3220  std::unique_ptr<TargetMachine> TM = createTargetMachine(F, OptLevel);
3221 
3222  FunctionAnalysisManager FAM;
3223  FAM.registerPass([]() { return TargetLibraryAnalysis(); });
3224  FAM.registerPass([]() { return AssumptionAnalysis(); });
3225  FAM.registerPass([]() { return DominatorTreeAnalysis(); });
3226  FAM.registerPass([]() { return LoopAnalysis(); });
3227  FAM.registerPass([]() { return ScalarEvolutionAnalysis(); });
3228  FAM.registerPass([]() { return PassInstrumentationAnalysis(); });
3229  TargetIRAnalysis TIRA;
3230  if (TM)
3231  TIRA = TargetIRAnalysis(
3232  [&](const Function &F) { return TM->getTargetTransformInfo(F); });
3233  FAM.registerPass([&]() { return TIRA; });
3234 
3235  TargetIRAnalysis::Result &&TTI = TIRA.run(*F, FAM);
3236  ScalarEvolutionAnalysis SEA;
3237  ScalarEvolution &&SE = SEA.run(*F, FAM);
3238  DominatorTreeAnalysis DTA;
3239  DominatorTree &&DT = DTA.run(*F, FAM);
3240  LoopAnalysis LIA;
3241  LoopInfo &&LI = LIA.run(*F, FAM);
3242  AssumptionAnalysis ACT;
3243  AssumptionCache &&AC = ACT.run(*F, FAM);
3244  OptimizationRemarkEmitter ORE{F};
3245 
3246  Loop *L = LI.getLoopFor(CLI->getHeader());
3247  assert(L && "Expecting CanonicalLoopInfo to be recognized as a loop");
3248 
3249  TargetTransformInfo::UnrollingPreferences UP =
3250  gatherUnrollingPreferences(L, SE, TTI,
3251  /*BlockFrequencyInfo=*/nullptr,
3252  /*ProfileSummaryInfo=*/nullptr, ORE, OptLevel,
3253  /*UserThreshold=*/std::nullopt,
3254  /*UserCount=*/std::nullopt,
3255  /*UserAllowPartial=*/true,
3256  /*UserAllowRuntime=*/true,
3257  /*UserUpperBound=*/std::nullopt,
3258  /*UserFullUnrollMaxCount=*/std::nullopt);
3259 
3260  UP.Force = true;
3261 
3262  // Account for additional optimizations taking place before the LoopUnrollPass
3263  // would unroll the loop.
3264  UP.Threshold *= UnrollThresholdFactor;
3265  UP.PartialThreshold *= UnrollThresholdFactor;
3266 
3267  // Use normal unroll factors even if the rest of the code is optimized for
3268  // size.
3269  UP.OptSizeThreshold = UP.Threshold;
3270  UP.PartialOptSizeThreshold = UP.PartialThreshold;
3271 
3272  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Unroll heuristic thresholds:\n"
3273  << " Threshold=" << UP.Threshold << "\n"
3274  << " PartialThreshold=" << UP.PartialThreshold << "\n"
3275  << " OptSizeThreshold=" << UP.OptSizeThreshold << "\n"
3276  << " PartialOptSizeThreshold="
3277  << UP.PartialOptSizeThreshold << "\n");
3278 
3279  // Disable peeling.
3280  TargetTransformInfo::PeelingPreferences PP =
3281  gatherPeelingPreferences(L, SE, TTI,
3282  /*UserAllowPeeling=*/false,
3283  /*UserAllowProfileBasedPeeling=*/false,
3284  /*UnrollingSpecficValues=*/false);
3285 
3286  SmallPtrSet<const Value *, 32> EphValues;
3287  CodeMetrics::collectEphemeralValues(L, &AC, EphValues);
3288 
3289  // Assume that reads and writes to stack variables can be eliminated by
3290  // Mem2Reg, SROA or LICM. That is, don't count them towards the loop body's
3291  // size.
3292  for (BasicBlock *BB : L->blocks()) {
3293  for (Instruction &I : *BB) {
3294  Value *Ptr;
3295  if (auto *Load = dyn_cast<LoadInst>(&I)) {
3296  Ptr = Load->getPointerOperand();
3297  } else if (auto *Store = dyn_cast<StoreInst>(&I)) {
3298  Ptr = Store->getPointerOperand();
3299  } else
3300  continue;
3301 
3302  Ptr = Ptr->stripPointerCasts();
3303 
3304  if (auto *Alloca = dyn_cast<AllocaInst>(Ptr)) {
3305  if (Alloca->getParent() == &F->getEntryBlock())
3306  EphValues.insert(&I);
3307  }
3308  }
3309  }
3310 
3311  unsigned NumInlineCandidates;
3312  bool NotDuplicatable;
3313  bool Convergent;
3314  InstructionCost LoopSizeIC =
3315  ApproximateLoopSize(L, NumInlineCandidates, NotDuplicatable, Convergent,
3316  TTI, EphValues, UP.BEInsns);
3317  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Estimated loop size is " << LoopSizeIC << "\n");
3318 
3319  // Loop is not unrollable if the loop contains certain instructions.
3320  if (NotDuplicatable || Convergent || !LoopSizeIC.isValid()) {
3321  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Loop not considered unrollable\n");
3322  return 1;
3323  }
3324  unsigned LoopSize = *LoopSizeIC.getValue();
3325 
3326  // TODO: Determine trip count of \p CLI if constant, computeUnrollCount might
3327  // be able to use it.
3328  int TripCount = 0;
3329  int MaxTripCount = 0;
3330  bool MaxOrZero = false;
3331  unsigned TripMultiple = 0;
3332 
3333  bool UseUpperBound = false;
3334  computeUnrollCount(L, TTI, DT, &LI, &AC, SE, EphValues, &ORE, TripCount,
3335  MaxTripCount, MaxOrZero, TripMultiple, LoopSize, UP, PP,
3336  UseUpperBound);
3337  unsigned Factor = UP.Count;
3338  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Suggesting unroll factor of " << Factor << "\n");
3339 
3340  // This function returns 1 to signal to not unroll a loop.
3341  if (Factor == 0)
3342  return 1;
3343  return Factor;
3344 }
3345 
3346 void OpenMPIRBuilder::unrollLoopPartial(DebugLoc DL, CanonicalLoopInfo *Loop,
3347  int32_t Factor,
3348  CanonicalLoopInfo **UnrolledCLI) {
3349  assert(Factor >= 0 && "Unroll factor must not be negative");
3350 
3351  Function *F = Loop->getFunction();
3352  LLVMContext &Ctx = F->getContext();
3353 
3354  // If the unrolled loop is not used for another loop-associated directive, it
3355  // is sufficient to add metadata for the LoopUnrollPass.
3356  if (!UnrolledCLI) {
3357  SmallVector<Metadata *, 2> LoopMetadata;
3358  LoopMetadata.push_back(
3359  MDNode::get(Ctx, MDString::get(Ctx, "llvm.loop.unroll.enable")));
3360 
3361  if (Factor >= 1) {
3362  ConstantAsMetadata *FactorConst = ConstantAsMetadata::get(
3363  ConstantInt::get(Type::getInt32Ty(Ctx), APInt(32, Factor)));
3364  LoopMetadata.push_back(MDNode::get(
3365  Ctx, {MDString::get(Ctx, "llvm.loop.unroll.count"), FactorConst}));
3366  }
3367 
3368  addLoopMetadata(Loop, LoopMetadata);
3369  return;
3370  }
3371 
3372  // Heuristically determine the unroll factor.
3373  if (Factor == 0)
3374  Factor = computeHeuristicUnrollFactor(Loop);
3375 
3376  // No change required with unroll factor 1.
3377  if (Factor == 1) {
3378  *UnrolledCLI = Loop;
3379  return;
3380  }
3381 
3382  assert(Factor >= 2 &&
3383  "unrolling only makes sense with a factor of 2 or larger");
3384 
3385  Type *IndVarTy = Loop->getIndVarType();
3386 
3387  // Apply partial unrolling by tiling the loop by the unroll-factor, then fully
3388  // unroll the inner loop.
3389  Value *FactorVal =
3390  ConstantInt::get(IndVarTy, APInt(IndVarTy->getIntegerBitWidth(), Factor,
3391  /*isSigned=*/false));
3392  std::vector<CanonicalLoopInfo *> LoopNest =
3393  tileLoops(DL, {Loop}, {FactorVal});
3394  assert(LoopNest.size() == 2 && "Expect 2 loops after tiling");
3395  *UnrolledCLI = LoopNest[0];
3396  CanonicalLoopInfo *InnerLoop = LoopNest[1];
3397 
3398  // LoopUnrollPass can only fully unroll loops with constant trip count.
3399  // Unroll by the unroll factor with a fallback epilog for the remainder
3400  // iterations if necessary.
3401  ConstantAsMetadata *FactorConst = ConstantAsMetadata::get(
3402  ConstantInt::get(Type::getInt32Ty(Ctx), APInt(32, Factor)));
3403  addLoopMetadata(
3404  InnerLoop,
3405  {MDNode::get(Ctx, MDString::get(Ctx, "llvm.loop.unroll.enable")),
3406  MDNode::get(
3407  Ctx, {MDString::get(Ctx, "llvm.loop.unroll.count"), FactorConst})});
3408 
3409 #ifndef NDEBUG
3410  (*UnrolledCLI)->assertOK();
3411 #endif
3412 }

3436 OpenMPIRBuilder::InsertPointTy OpenMPIRBuilder::createSingle(
3437  const LocationDescription &Loc, BodyGenCallbackTy BodyGenCB,
3438  FinalizeCallbackTy FiniCB, bool IsNowait, llvm::Value *DidIt) {
3439 
3440  if (!updateToLocation(Loc))
3441  return Loc.IP;
3442 
3443  // If needed (i.e. not null), initialize `DidIt` with 0
3444  if (DidIt) {
3445  Builder.CreateStore(Builder.getInt32(0), DidIt);
3446  }
3447 
3448  Directive OMPD = Directive::OMPD_single;
3449  uint32_t SrcLocStrSize;
3450  Constant *SrcLocStr = getOrCreateSrcLocStr(Loc, SrcLocStrSize);
3451  Value *Ident = getOrCreateIdent(SrcLocStr, SrcLocStrSize);
3452  Value *ThreadId = getOrCreateThreadID(Ident);
3453  Value *Args[] = {Ident, ThreadId};
3454 
3455  Function *EntryRTLFn = getOrCreateRuntimeFunctionPtr(OMPRTL___kmpc_single);
3456  Instruction *EntryCall = Builder.CreateCall(EntryRTLFn, Args);
3457 
3458  Function *ExitRTLFn = getOrCreateRuntimeFunctionPtr(OMPRTL___kmpc_end_single);
3459  Instruction *ExitCall = Builder.CreateCall(ExitRTLFn, Args);
3460 
3461  // generates the following:
3462  // if (__kmpc_single()) {
3463  // .... single region ...
3464  // __kmpc_end_single
3465  // }
3466  // __kmpc_barrier
3467 
3468  EmitOMPInlinedRegion(OMPD, EntryCall, ExitCall, BodyGenCB, FiniCB,
3469  /*Conditional*/ true,
3470  /*hasFinalize*/ true);
3471  if (!IsNowait)
3472  createBarrier(LocationDescription(Builder.saveIP(), Loc.DL),
3473  omp::Directive::OMPD_unknown, /* ForceSimpleCall */ false,
3474  /* CheckCancelFlag */ false);
3475  return Builder.saveIP();
3476 }

3478 OpenMPIRBuilder::InsertPointTy OpenMPIRBuilder::createCritical(
3479  const LocationDescription &Loc, BodyGenCallbackTy BodyGenCB,
3480  FinalizeCallbackTy FiniCB, StringRef CriticalName, Value *HintInst) {
3481 
3482  if (!updateToLocation(Loc))
3483  return Loc.IP;
3484 
3485  Directive OMPD = Directive::OMPD_critical;
3486  uint32_t SrcLocStrSize;

3488  Value *Ident = getOrCreateIdent(SrcLocStr, SrcLocStrSize);
3489  Value *ThreadId = getOrCreateThreadID(Ident);
3490  Value *LockVar = getOMPCriticalRegionLock(CriticalName);
3491  Value *Args[] = {Ident, ThreadId, LockVar};
3492

3494  Function *RTFn = nullptr;

3497  EnterArgs.push_back(HintInst);

3499  } else {
3500  RTFn = getOrCreateRuntimeFunctionPtr(OMPRTL___kmpc_critical);
3501  }
3502  Instruction *EntryCall = Builder.CreateCall(RTFn, EnterArgs);
3503 
3504  Function *ExitRTLFn =
3505  getOrCreateRuntimeFunctionPtr(OMPRTL___kmpc_end_critical);
3506  Instruction *ExitCall = Builder.CreateCall(ExitRTLFn, Args);
3507 
3508  return EmitOMPInlinedRegion(OMPD, EntryCall, ExitCall, BodyGenCB, FiniCB,
3509  /*Conditional*/ false, /*hasFinalize*/ true);
3510 }

3512 OpenMPIRBuilder::InsertPointTy
3513 OpenMPIRBuilder::createOrderedDepend(const LocationDescription &Loc,
3514  InsertPointTy AllocaIP, unsigned NumLoops,
3515  ArrayRef<llvm::Value *> StoreValues,
3516  const Twine &Name, bool IsDependSource) {
3517  assert(
3518  llvm::all_of(StoreValues,
3519  [](Value *SV) { return SV->getType()->isIntegerTy(64); }) &&
3520  "OpenMP runtime requires depend vec with i64 type");
3521 
3522  if (!updateToLocation(Loc))
3523  return Loc.IP;
3524 
3525  // Allocate space for vector and generate alloc instruction.
3526  auto *ArrI64Ty = ArrayType::get(Int64, NumLoops);
3527  Builder.restoreIP(AllocaIP);
3528  AllocaInst *ArgsBase = Builder.CreateAlloca(ArrI64Ty, nullptr, Name);
3529  ArgsBase->setAlignment(Align(8));
3530  Builder.restoreIP(Loc.IP);
3531 
3532  // Store the index value with offset in depend vector.
3533  for (unsigned I = 0; I < NumLoops; ++I) {
3534  Value *DependAddrGEPIter = Builder.CreateInBoundsGEP(
3535  ArrI64Ty, ArgsBase, {Builder.getInt64(0), Builder.getInt64(I)});
3536  StoreInst *STInst = Builder.CreateStore(StoreValues[I], DependAddrGEPIter);
3537  STInst->setAlignment(Align(8));
3538  }
3539 
3540  Value *DependBaseAddrGEP = Builder.CreateInBoundsGEP(
3541  ArrI64Ty, ArgsBase, {Builder.getInt64(0), Builder.getInt64(0)});
3542 
3543  uint32_t SrcLocStrSize;
3544  Constant *SrcLocStr = getOrCreateSrcLocStr(Loc, SrcLocStrSize);
3545  Value *Ident = getOrCreateIdent(SrcLocStr, SrcLocStrSize);
3546  Value *ThreadId = getOrCreateThreadID(Ident);
3547  Value *Args[] = {Ident, ThreadId, DependBaseAddrGEP};
3548 
3549  Function *RTLFn = nullptr;
3550  if (IsDependSource)
3551  RTLFn = getOrCreateRuntimeFunctionPtr(OMPRTL___kmpc_doacross_post);
3552  else
3553  RTLFn = getOrCreateRuntimeFunctionPtr(OMPRTL___kmpc_doacross_wait);
3554  Builder.CreateCall(RTLFn, Args);
3555 
3556  return Builder.saveIP();
3557 }

3570  uint32_t SrcLocStrSize;

3587 
3588 OpenMPIRBuilder::InsertPointTy OpenMPIRBuilder::EmitOMPInlinedRegion(
3589  Directive OMPD, Instruction *EntryCall, Instruction *ExitCall,
3590  BodyGenCallbackTy BodyGenCB, FinalizeCallbackTy FiniCB, bool Conditional,
3591  bool HasFinalize, bool IsCancellable) {
3592 
3593  if (HasFinalize)
3594  FinalizationStack.push_back({FiniCB, OMPD, IsCancellable});
3595 
3596  // Create inlined region's entry and body blocks, in preparation
3597  // for conditional creation
3598  BasicBlock *EntryBB = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
3599  Instruction *SplitPos = EntryBB->getTerminator();
3600  if (!isa_and_nonnull<BranchInst>(SplitPos))
3601  SplitPos = new UnreachableInst(Builder.getContext(), EntryBB);
3602  BasicBlock *ExitBB = EntryBB->splitBasicBlock(SplitPos, "omp_region.end");
3603  BasicBlock *FiniBB =
3604  EntryBB->splitBasicBlock(EntryBB->getTerminator(), "omp_region.finalize");
3605 
3606  Builder.SetInsertPoint(EntryBB->getTerminator());
3607  emitCommonDirectiveEntry(OMPD, EntryCall, ExitBB, Conditional);
3608 
3609  // generate body
3610  BodyGenCB(/* AllocaIP */ InsertPointTy(),
3611  /* CodeGenIP */ Builder.saveIP());
3612 
3613  // emit exit call and do any needed finalization.
3614  auto FinIP = InsertPointTy(FiniBB, FiniBB->getFirstInsertionPt());
3615  assert(FiniBB->getTerminator()->getNumSuccessors() == 1 &&
3616  FiniBB->getTerminator()->getSuccessor(0) == ExitBB &&
3617  "Unexpected control flow graph state!!");
3618  emitCommonDirectiveExit(OMPD, FinIP, ExitCall, HasFinalize);
3619  assert(FiniBB->getUniquePredecessor()->getUniqueSuccessor() == FiniBB &&
3620  "Unexpected Control Flow State!");
3621  MergeBlockIntoPredecessor(FiniBB);
3622 
3623  // If we are skipping the region of a non conditional, remove the exit
3624  // block, and clear the builder's insertion point.
3625  assert(SplitPos->getParent() == ExitBB &&
3626  "Unexpected Insertion point location!");
3627  auto merged = MergeBlockIntoPredecessor(ExitBB);
3628  BasicBlock *ExitPredBB = SplitPos->getParent();
3629  auto InsertBB = merged ? ExitPredBB : ExitBB;
3630  if (!isa_and_nonnull<BranchInst>(SplitPos))
3631  SplitPos->eraseFromParent();
3632  Builder.SetInsertPoint(InsertBB);
3633 
3634  return Builder.saveIP();
3635 }
3636 
3637 OpenMPIRBuilder::InsertPointTy OpenMPIRBuilder::emitCommonDirectiveEntry(
3638  Directive OMPD, Value *EntryCall, BasicBlock *ExitBB, bool Conditional) {
3639  // if nothing to do, Return current insertion point.
3640  if (!Conditional || !EntryCall)
3641  return Builder.saveIP();
3642 
3643  BasicBlock *EntryBB = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
3644  Value *CallBool = Builder.CreateIsNotNull(EntryCall);
3645  auto *ThenBB = BasicBlock::Create(M.getContext(), "omp_region.body");
3646  auto *UI = new UnreachableInst(Builder.getContext(), ThenBB);
3647 
3648  // Emit thenBB and set the Builder's insertion point there for
3649  // body generation next. Place the block after the current block.
3650  Function *CurFn = EntryBB->getParent();
3651  CurFn->insert(std::next(EntryBB->getIterator()), ThenBB);
3652 
3653  // Move Entry branch to end of ThenBB, and replace with conditional
3654  // branch (If-stmt)
3655  Instruction *EntryBBTI = EntryBB->getTerminator();
3656  Builder.CreateCondBr(CallBool, ThenBB, ExitBB);
3657  EntryBBTI->removeFromParent();
3658  Builder.SetInsertPoint(UI);
3659  Builder.Insert(EntryBBTI);
3660  UI->eraseFromParent();
3661  Builder.SetInsertPoint(ThenBB->getTerminator());
3662 
3663  // return an insertion point to ExitBB.
3664  return IRBuilder<>::InsertPoint(ExitBB, ExitBB->getFirstInsertionPt());
3665 }
3666 
3667 OpenMPIRBuilder::InsertPointTy OpenMPIRBuilder::emitCommonDirectiveExit(
3668  omp::Directive OMPD, InsertPointTy FinIP, Instruction *ExitCall,
3669  bool HasFinalize) {
3670 
3671  Builder.restoreIP(FinIP);
3672 
3673  // If there is finalization to do, emit it before the exit call
3674  if (HasFinalize) {
3675  assert(!FinalizationStack.empty() &&
3676  "Unexpected finalization stack state!");
3677 
3678  FinalizationInfo Fi = FinalizationStack.pop_back_val();
3679  assert(Fi.DK == OMPD && "Unexpected Directive for Finalization call!");
3680 
3681  Fi.FiniCB(FinIP);
3682 
3683  BasicBlock *FiniBB = FinIP.getBlock();
3684  Instruction *FiniBBTI = FiniBB->getTerminator();
3685 
3686  // set Builder IP for call creation
3687  Builder.SetInsertPoint(FiniBBTI);
3688  }
3689 
3690  if (!ExitCall)
3691  return Builder.saveIP();
3692 
3693  // place the Exitcall as last instruction before Finalization block terminator
3694  ExitCall->removeFromParent();
3695  Builder.Insert(ExitCall);
3696 
3697  return IRBuilder<>::InsertPoint(ExitCall->getParent(),
3698  ExitCall->getIterator());
3699 }
3700 
3701 OpenMPIRBuilder::InsertPointTy OpenMPIRBuilder::createCopyinClauseBlocks(
3702  InsertPointTy IP, Value *MasterAddr, Value *PrivateAddr,
3703  llvm::IntegerType *IntPtrTy, bool BranchtoEnd) {
3704  if (!IP.isSet())
3705  return IP;
3706 
3707  IRBuilder<>::InsertPointGuard IPG(Builder);
3708 
3709  // creates the following CFG structure
3710  // OMP_Entry : (MasterAddr != PrivateAddr)?
3711  // F T
3712  // | \
3713  // | copin.not.master
3714  // | /
3715  // v /
3716  // copyin.not.master.end
3717  // |
3718  // v
3719  // OMP.Entry.Next
3720 
3721  BasicBlock *OMP_Entry = IP.getBlock();
3722  Function *CurFn = OMP_Entry->getParent();
3723  BasicBlock *CopyBegin =
3724  BasicBlock::Create(M.getContext(), "copyin.not.master", CurFn);
3725  BasicBlock *CopyEnd = nullptr;
3726 
3727  // If entry block is terminated, split to preserve the branch to following
3728  // basic block (i.e. OMP.Entry.Next), otherwise, leave everything as is.
3729  if (isa_and_nonnull<BranchInst>(OMP_Entry->getTerminator())) {
3730  CopyEnd = OMP_Entry->splitBasicBlock(OMP_Entry->getTerminator(),
3731  "copyin.not.master.end");
3732  OMP_Entry->getTerminator()->eraseFromParent();
3733  } else {
3734  CopyEnd =
3735  BasicBlock::Create(M.getContext(), "copyin.not.master.end", CurFn);
3736  }
3737 
3738  Builder.SetInsertPoint(OMP_Entry);
3739  Value *MasterPtr = Builder.CreatePtrToInt(MasterAddr, IntPtrTy);
3740  Value *PrivatePtr = Builder.CreatePtrToInt(PrivateAddr, IntPtrTy);
3741  Value *cmp = Builder.CreateICmpNE(MasterPtr, PrivatePtr);
3742  Builder.CreateCondBr(cmp, CopyBegin, CopyEnd);
3743 
3744  Builder.SetInsertPoint(CopyBegin);
3745  if (BranchtoEnd)
3746  Builder.SetInsertPoint(Builder.CreateBr(CopyEnd));
3747 
3748  return Builder.saveIP();
3749 }

3812 CallInst *OpenMPIRBuilder::createOMPInteropDestroy(
3813  const LocationDescription &Loc, Value *InteropVar, Value *Device,
3814  Value *NumDependences, Value *DependenceAddress, bool HaveNowaitClause) {
3815  IRBuilder<>::InsertPointGuard IPG(Builder);
3816  Builder.restoreIP(Loc.IP);
3817 
3818  uint32_t SrcLocStrSize;
3819  Constant *SrcLocStr = getOrCreateSrcLocStr(Loc, SrcLocStrSize);
3820  Value *Ident = getOrCreateIdent(SrcLocStr, SrcLocStrSize);
3821  Value *ThreadId = getOrCreateThreadID(Ident);
3822  if (Device == nullptr)
3823  Device = ConstantInt::get(Int32, -1);
3824  if (NumDependences == nullptr) {
3825  NumDependences = ConstantInt::get(Int32, 0);
3826  PointerType *PointerTypeVar = Type::getInt8PtrTy(M.getContext());
3827  DependenceAddress = ConstantPointerNull::get(PointerTypeVar);
3828  }
3829  Value *HaveNowaitClauseVal = ConstantInt::get(Int32, HaveNowaitClause);
3830  Value *Args[] = {
3831  Ident, ThreadId, InteropVar, Device,
3832  NumDependences, DependenceAddress, HaveNowaitClauseVal};
3833 
3834  Function *Fn = getOrCreateRuntimeFunctionPtr(OMPRTL___tgt_interop_destroy);
3835 
3836  return Builder.CreateCall(Fn, Args);
3837 }

3839 CallInst *OpenMPIRBuilder::createOMPInteropUse(const LocationDescription &Loc,
3840  Value *InteropVar, Value *Device,
3841  Value *NumDependences,
3842  Value *DependenceAddress,
3843  bool HaveNowaitClause) {
3844  IRBuilder<>::InsertPointGuard IPG(Builder);
3845  Builder.restoreIP(Loc.IP);

3855  DependenceAddress = ConstantPointerNull::get(PointerTypeVar);
3856  }

3858  Value *Args[] = {
3859  Ident, ThreadId, InteropVar, Device,
3860  NumDependences, DependenceAddress, HaveNowaitClauseVal};
3861 
3862  Function *Fn = getOrCreateRuntimeFunctionPtr(OMPRTL___tgt_interop_use);
3863 
3864  return Builder.CreateCall(Fn, Args);
3865 }

3886 
3887 OpenMPIRBuilder::InsertPointTy
3888 OpenMPIRBuilder::createTargetInit(const LocationDescription &Loc, bool IsSPMD) {
3889  if (!updateToLocation(Loc))
3890  return Loc.IP;
3891 
3892  uint32_t SrcLocStrSize;
3893  Constant *SrcLocStr = getOrCreateSrcLocStr(Loc, SrcLocStrSize);
3894  Constant *Ident = getOrCreateIdent(SrcLocStr, SrcLocStrSize);
3895  ConstantInt *IsSPMDVal = ConstantInt::getSigned(
3896  IntegerType::getInt8Ty(Int8->getContext()),
3897  IsSPMD ? OMP_TGT_EXEC_MODE_SPMD : OMP_TGT_EXEC_MODE_GENERIC);
3898  ConstantInt *UseGenericStateMachine =
3899  ConstantInt::getBool(Int32->getContext(), !IsSPMD);
3900 
3901  Function *Fn = getOrCreateRuntimeFunctionPtr(
3902  omp::RuntimeFunction::OMPRTL___kmpc_target_init);
3903 
3904  CallInst *ThreadKind = Builder.CreateCall(
3905  Fn, {Ident, IsSPMDVal, UseGenericStateMachine});
3906 
3907  Value *ExecUserCode = Builder.CreateICmpEQ(
3908  ThreadKind, ConstantInt::get(ThreadKind->getType(), -1),
3909  "exec_user_code");
3910 
3911  // ThreadKind = __kmpc_target_init(...)
3912  // if (ThreadKind == -1)
3913  // user_code
3914  // else
3915  // return;
3916 
3917  auto *UI = Builder.CreateUnreachable();
3918  BasicBlock *CheckBB = UI->getParent();
3919  BasicBlock *UserCodeEntryBB = CheckBB->splitBasicBlock(UI, "user_code.entry");
3920 
3921  BasicBlock *WorkerExitBB = BasicBlock::Create(
3922  CheckBB->getContext(), "worker.exit", CheckBB->getParent());
3923  Builder.SetInsertPoint(WorkerExitBB);
3924  Builder.CreateRetVoid();
3925 
3926  auto *CheckBBTI = CheckBB->getTerminator();
3927  Builder.SetInsertPoint(CheckBBTI);
3928  Builder.CreateCondBr(ExecUserCode, UI->getParent(), WorkerExitBB);
3929 
3930  CheckBBTI->eraseFromParent();
3931  UI->eraseFromParent();
3932 
3933  // Continue in the "user_code" block, see diagram above and in
3934  // openmp/libomptarget/deviceRTLs/common/include/target.h .
3935  return InsertPointTy(UserCodeEntryBB, UserCodeEntryBB->getFirstInsertionPt());
3936 }

3956 void OpenMPIRBuilder::setOutlinedTargetRegionFunctionAttributes(
3957  Function *OutlinedFn, int32_t NumTeams, int32_t NumThreads) {
3958  if (Config.isEmbedded()) {
3959  OutlinedFn->setLinkage(GlobalValue::WeakODRLinkage);
3960  // TODO: Determine if DSO local can be set to true.
3961  OutlinedFn->setDSOLocal(false);
3962  OutlinedFn->setVisibility(GlobalValue::ProtectedVisibility);
3963  if (Triple(M.getTargetTriple()).isAMDGCN())
3964  OutlinedFn->setCallingConv(CallingConv::AMDGPU_KERNEL);
3965  }

3968  OutlinedFn->addFnAttr("omp_target_num_teams", std::to_string(NumTeams));
3969  if (NumThreads > 0)
3970  OutlinedFn->addFnAttr("omp_target_thread_limit",
3971  std::to_string(NumThreads));
3972 }

3986 Constant *OpenMPIRBuilder::createTargetRegionEntryAddr(Function *OutlinedFn,
3987  StringRef EntryFnName) {
3988  if (OutlinedFn)
3989  return OutlinedFn;
3990 
3991  assert(!M.getGlobalVariable(EntryFnName, true) &&
3992  "Named kernel already exists?");
3993  return new GlobalVariable(
3994  M, Builder.getInt8Ty(), /*isConstant=*/true, GlobalValue::InternalLinkage,

3998 void OpenMPIRBuilder::emitTargetRegionFunction(
3999  OffloadEntriesInfoManager &InfoManager, TargetRegionEntryInfo &EntryInfo,
4000  FunctionGenCallback &GenerateFunctionCallback, int32_t NumTeams,
4001  int32_t NumThreads, bool IsOffloadEntry, Function *&OutlinedFn,
4002  Constant *&OutlinedFnID) {
4003 
4004  SmallString<64> EntryFnName;
4005  InfoManager.getTargetRegionEntryFnName(EntryFnName, EntryInfo);
4006 
4007  OutlinedFn = Config.isEmbedded() || !Config.openMPOffloadMandatory()
4008  ? GenerateFunctionCallback(EntryFnName)
4009  : nullptr;
4010 
4011  // If this target outline function is not an offload entry, we don't need to
4012  // register it. This may be in the case of a false if clause, or if there are
4013  // no OpenMP targets.
4014  if (!IsOffloadEntry)
4015  return;
4016 
4017  std::string EntryFnIDName =
4018  Config.isEmbedded()
4019  ? std::string(EntryFnName)
4020  : createPlatformSpecificName({EntryFnName, "region_id"});
4021 
4022  OutlinedFnID = registerTargetRegionFunction(
4023  InfoManager, EntryInfo, OutlinedFn, EntryFnName, EntryFnIDName, NumTeams,
4024  NumThreads);
4025 }
4026 
4027 Constant *OpenMPIRBuilder::registerTargetRegionFunction(
4028  OffloadEntriesInfoManager &InfoManager, TargetRegionEntryInfo &EntryInfo,
4029  Function *OutlinedFn, StringRef EntryFnName, StringRef EntryFnIDName,
4030  int32_t NumTeams, int32_t NumThreads) {
4031  if (OutlinedFn)
4032  setOutlinedTargetRegionFunctionAttributes(OutlinedFn, NumTeams, NumThreads);
4033  auto OutlinedFnID = createOutlinedFunctionID(OutlinedFn, EntryFnIDName);
4034  auto EntryAddr = createTargetRegionEntryAddr(OutlinedFn, EntryFnName);
4035  InfoManager.registerTargetRegionEntryInfo(
4036  EntryInfo, EntryAddr, OutlinedFnID,
4037  OffloadEntriesInfoManager::OMPTargetRegionEntryTargetRegion);
4038  return OutlinedFnID;
4039 }

4041 std::string OpenMPIRBuilder::getNameWithSeparators(ArrayRef<StringRef> Parts,
4042  StringRef FirstSeparator,
4043  StringRef Separator) {
4044  SmallString<128> Buffer;
4045  llvm::raw_svector_ostream OS(Buffer);
4046  StringRef Sep = FirstSeparator;
4047  for (StringRef Part : Parts) {
4048  OS << Sep << Part;
4049  Sep = Separator;
4050  }
4051  return OS.str().str();
4052 }

4057  Config.separator());
4058 }

4060 GlobalVariable *
4061 OpenMPIRBuilder::getOrCreateInternalVariable(Type *Ty, const StringRef &Name,
4062  unsigned AddressSpace) {
4063  auto &Elem = *InternalVars.try_emplace(Name, nullptr).first;
4064  if (Elem.second) {
4065  assert(cast<PointerType>(Elem.second->getType())
4066  ->isOpaqueOrPointeeTypeMatches(Ty) &&
4067  "OMP internal variable has different type than requested");
4068  } else {
4069  // TODO: investigate the appropriate linkage type used for the global
4070  // variable for possibly changing that to internal or private, or maybe
4071  // create different versions of the function for different OMP internal
4072  // variables.
4073  Elem.second = new GlobalVariable(
4074  M, Ty, /*IsConstant=*/false, GlobalValue::CommonLinkage,
4075  Constant::getNullValue(Ty), Elem.first(),
4076  /*InsertBefore=*/nullptr, GlobalValue::NotThreadLocal, AddressSpace);
4077  }
4078 
4079  return cast<GlobalVariable>(&*Elem.second);
4080 }

4101 void OpenMPIRBuilder::createMapperAllocas(const LocationDescription &Loc,
4102  InsertPointTy AllocaIP,
4103  unsigned NumOperands,
4104  struct MapperAllocas &MapperAllocas) {
4105  if (!updateToLocation(Loc))
4106  return;
4107 
4108  auto *ArrI8PtrTy = ArrayType::get(Int8Ptr, NumOperands);
4109  auto *ArrI64Ty = ArrayType::get(Int64, NumOperands);
4110  Builder.restoreIP(AllocaIP);
4111  AllocaInst *ArgsBase = Builder.CreateAlloca(ArrI8PtrTy);
4112  AllocaInst *Args = Builder.CreateAlloca(ArrI8PtrTy);
4113  AllocaInst *ArgSizes = Builder.CreateAlloca(ArrI64Ty);
4114  Builder.restoreIP(Loc.IP);
4115  MapperAllocas.ArgsBase = ArgsBase;
4116  MapperAllocas.Args = Args;
4117  MapperAllocas.ArgSizes = ArgSizes;

4120 void OpenMPIRBuilder::emitMapperCall(const LocationDescription &Loc,
4121  Function *MapperFunc, Value *SrcLocInfo,
4122  Value *MaptypesArg, Value *MapnamesArg,
4123  struct MapperAllocas &MapperAllocas,
4124  int64_t DeviceID, unsigned NumOperands) {
4125  if (!updateToLocation(Loc))
4126  return;
4127 
4128  auto *ArrI8PtrTy = ArrayType::get(Int8Ptr, NumOperands);
4129  auto *ArrI64Ty = ArrayType::get(Int64, NumOperands);
4130  Value *ArgsBaseGEP =
4131  Builder.CreateInBoundsGEP(ArrI8PtrTy, MapperAllocas.ArgsBase,
4132  {Builder.getInt32(0), Builder.getInt32(0)});
4133  Value *ArgsGEP =
4134  Builder.CreateInBoundsGEP(ArrI8PtrTy, MapperAllocas.Args,
4135  {Builder.getInt32(0), Builder.getInt32(0)});
4136  Value *ArgSizesGEP =
4137  Builder.CreateInBoundsGEP(ArrI64Ty, MapperAllocas.ArgSizes,
4138  {Builder.getInt32(0), Builder.getInt32(0)});
4139  Value *NullPtr = Constant::getNullValue(Int8Ptr->getPointerTo());
4140  Builder.CreateCall(MapperFunc,
4141  {SrcLocInfo, Builder.getInt64(DeviceID),
4142  Builder.getInt32(NumOperands), ArgsBaseGEP, ArgsGEP,
4143  ArgSizesGEP, MaptypesArg, MapnamesArg, NullPtr});
4144 }

4146 void OpenMPIRBuilder::emitOffloadingArraysArgument(IRBuilderBase &Builder,
4147  TargetDataRTArgs &RTArgs,
4148  TargetDataInfo &Info,
4149  bool EmitDebug,
4150  bool ForEndCall) {
4151  assert((!ForEndCall || Info.separateBeginEndCalls()) &&
4152  "expected region end call to runtime only when end call is separate");
4153  auto VoidPtrTy = Type::getInt8PtrTy(M.getContext());
4154  auto VoidPtrPtrTy = VoidPtrTy->getPointerTo(0);
4155  auto Int64Ty = Type::getInt64Ty(M.getContext());
4156  auto Int64PtrTy = Type::getInt64PtrTy(M.getContext());
4157 
4158  if (!Info.NumberOfPtrs) {
4159  RTArgs.BasePointersArray = ConstantPointerNull::get(VoidPtrPtrTy);
4160  RTArgs.PointersArray = ConstantPointerNull::get(VoidPtrPtrTy);
4161  RTArgs.SizesArray = ConstantPointerNull::get(Int64PtrTy);
4162  RTArgs.MapTypesArray = ConstantPointerNull::get(Int64PtrTy);
4163  RTArgs.MapNamesArray = ConstantPointerNull::get(VoidPtrPtrTy);
4164  RTArgs.MappersArray = ConstantPointerNull::get(VoidPtrPtrTy);
4165  return;
4166  }
4167 
4168  RTArgs.BasePointersArray = Builder.CreateConstInBoundsGEP2_32(
4169  ArrayType::get(VoidPtrTy, Info.NumberOfPtrs),
4170  Info.RTArgs.BasePointersArray,
4171  /*Idx0=*/0, /*Idx1=*/0);
4172  RTArgs.PointersArray = Builder.CreateConstInBoundsGEP2_32(
4173  ArrayType::get(VoidPtrTy, Info.NumberOfPtrs), Info.RTArgs.PointersArray,
4174  /*Idx0=*/0,
4175  /*Idx1=*/0);
4176  RTArgs.SizesArray = Builder.CreateConstInBoundsGEP2_32(
4177  ArrayType::get(Int64Ty, Info.NumberOfPtrs), Info.RTArgs.SizesArray,
4178  /*Idx0=*/0, /*Idx1=*/0);
4179  RTArgs.MapTypesArray = Builder.CreateConstInBoundsGEP2_32(
4180  ArrayType::get(Int64Ty, Info.NumberOfPtrs),
4181  ForEndCall && Info.RTArgs.MapTypesArrayEnd ? Info.RTArgs.MapTypesArrayEnd
4182  : Info.RTArgs.MapTypesArray,
4183  /*Idx0=*/0,
4184  /*Idx1=*/0);
4185 
4186  // Only emit the mapper information arrays if debug information is
4187  // requested.
4188  if (!EmitDebug)
4189  RTArgs.MapNamesArray = ConstantPointerNull::get(VoidPtrPtrTy);
4190  else
4191  RTArgs.MapNamesArray = Builder.CreateConstInBoundsGEP2_32(
4192  ArrayType::get(VoidPtrTy, Info.NumberOfPtrs), Info.RTArgs.MapNamesArray,
4193  /*Idx0=*/0,
4194  /*Idx1=*/0);
4195  // If there is no user-defined mapper, set the mapper array to nullptr to
4196  // avoid an unnecessary data privatization
4197  if (!Info.HasMapper)
4198  RTArgs.MappersArray = ConstantPointerNull::get(VoidPtrPtrTy);
4199  else
4200  RTArgs.MappersArray =
4201  Builder.CreatePointerCast(Info.RTArgs.MappersArray, VoidPtrPtrTy);
4202 }
4203 
4204 bool OpenMPIRBuilder::checkAndEmitFlushAfterAtomic(
4205  const LocationDescription &Loc, llvm::AtomicOrdering AO, AtomicKind AK) {
4206  assert(!(AO == AtomicOrdering::NotAtomic ||
4207  AO == llvm::AtomicOrdering::Unordered) &&
4208  "Unexpected Atomic Ordering.");
4209 
4210  bool Flush = false;
4211  llvm::AtomicOrdering FlushAO = AtomicOrdering::Monotonic;
4212 
4213  switch (AK) {
4214  case Read:
4215  if (AO == AtomicOrdering::Acquire || AO == AtomicOrdering::AcquireRelease ||
4216  AO == AtomicOrdering::SequentiallyConsistent) {
4217  FlushAO = AtomicOrdering::Acquire;
4218  Flush = true;
4219  }
4220  break;
4221  case Write:
4222  case Compare:
4223  case Update:
4224  if (AO == AtomicOrdering::Release || AO == AtomicOrdering::AcquireRelease ||
4225  AO == AtomicOrdering::SequentiallyConsistent) {
4226  FlushAO = AtomicOrdering::Release;
4227  Flush = true;
4228  }
4229  break;
4230  case Capture:
4231  switch (AO) {
4232  case AtomicOrdering::Acquire:
4233  FlushAO = AtomicOrdering::Acquire;
4234  Flush = true;
4235  break;
4236  case AtomicOrdering::Release:
4237  FlushAO = AtomicOrdering::Release;
4238  Flush = true;
4239  break;
4240  case AtomicOrdering::AcquireRelease:
4241  case AtomicOrdering::SequentiallyConsistent:
4242  FlushAO = AtomicOrdering::AcquireRelease;
4243  Flush = true;
4244  break;
4245  default:
4246  // do nothing - leave silently.
4247  break;
4248  }
4249  }
4250 
4251  if (Flush) {
4252  // Currently Flush RT call still doesn't take memory_ordering, so for when
4253  // that happens, this tries to do the resolution of which atomic ordering
4254  // to use with but issue the flush call
4255  // TODO: pass `FlushAO` after memory ordering support is added
4256  (void)FlushAO;
4257  emitFlush(Loc);
4258  }
4259 
4260  // for AO == AtomicOrdering::Monotonic and all other case combinations
4261  // do nothing
4262  return Flush;
4263 }
4264 
4265 OpenMPIRBuilder::InsertPointTy
4266 OpenMPIRBuilder::createAtomicRead(const LocationDescription &Loc,
4267  AtomicOpValue &X, AtomicOpValue &V,
4268  AtomicOrdering AO) {
4269  if (!updateToLocation(Loc))
4270  return Loc.IP;
4271 
4272  Type *XTy = X.Var->getType();
4273  assert(XTy->isPointerTy() && "OMP Atomic expects a pointer to target memory");
4274  Type *XElemTy = X.ElemTy;
4275  assert((XElemTy->isFloatingPointTy() || XElemTy->isIntegerTy() ||
4276  XElemTy->isPointerTy()) &&
4277  "OMP atomic read expected a scalar type");
4278 
4279  Value *XRead = nullptr;
4280 
4281  if (XElemTy->isIntegerTy()) {
4282  LoadInst *XLD =
4283  Builder.CreateLoad(XElemTy, X.Var, X.IsVolatile, "omp.atomic.read");
4284  XLD->setAtomic(AO);
4285  XRead = cast<Value>(XLD);
4286  } else {
4287  // We need to bitcast and perform atomic op as integer
4288  unsigned Addrspace = cast<PointerType>(XTy)->getAddressSpace();
4289  IntegerType *IntCastTy =
4290  IntegerType::get(M.getContext(), XElemTy->getScalarSizeInBits());
4291  Value *XBCast = Builder.CreateBitCast(
4292  X.Var, IntCastTy->getPointerTo(Addrspace), "atomic.src.int.cast");
4293  LoadInst *XLoad =
4294  Builder.CreateLoad(IntCastTy, XBCast, X.IsVolatile, "omp.atomic.load");
4295  XLoad->setAtomic(AO);
4296  if (XElemTy->isFloatingPointTy()) {
4297  XRead = Builder.CreateBitCast(XLoad, XElemTy, "atomic.flt.cast");
4298  } else {
4299  XRead = Builder.CreateIntToPtr(XLoad, XElemTy, "atomic.ptr.cast");
4300  }
4301  }
4302  checkAndEmitFlushAfterAtomic(Loc, AO, AtomicKind::Read);
4303  Builder.CreateStore(XRead, V.Var, V.IsVolatile);
4304  return Builder.saveIP();
4305 }
4306 
4307 OpenMPIRBuilder::InsertPointTy
4308 OpenMPIRBuilder::createAtomicWrite(const LocationDescription &Loc,
4309  AtomicOpValue &X, Value *Expr,
4310  AtomicOrdering AO) {
4311  if (!updateToLocation(Loc))
4312  return Loc.IP;
4313 
4314  Type *XTy = X.Var->getType();
4315  assert(XTy->isPointerTy() && "OMP Atomic expects a pointer to target memory");
4316  Type *XElemTy = X.ElemTy;
4317  assert((XElemTy->isFloatingPointTy() || XElemTy->isIntegerTy() ||
4318  XElemTy->isPointerTy()) &&
4319  "OMP atomic write expected a scalar type");
4320 
4321  if (XElemTy->isIntegerTy()) {
4322  StoreInst *XSt = Builder.CreateStore(Expr, X.Var, X.IsVolatile);
4323  XSt->setAtomic(AO);
4324  } else {
4325  // We need to bitcast and perform atomic op as integers
4326  unsigned Addrspace = cast<PointerType>(XTy)->getAddressSpace();
4327  IntegerType *IntCastTy =
4328  IntegerType::get(M.getContext(), XElemTy->getScalarSizeInBits());
4329  Value *XBCast = Builder.CreateBitCast(
4330  X.Var, IntCastTy->getPointerTo(Addrspace), "atomic.dst.int.cast");
4331  Value *ExprCast =
4332  Builder.CreateBitCast(Expr, IntCastTy, "atomic.src.int.cast");
4333  StoreInst *XSt = Builder.CreateStore(ExprCast, XBCast, X.IsVolatile);
4334  XSt->setAtomic(AO);
4335  }
4336 
4337  checkAndEmitFlushAfterAtomic(Loc, AO, AtomicKind::Write);
4338  return Builder.saveIP();
4339 }
4340 
4341 OpenMPIRBuilder::InsertPointTy OpenMPIRBuilder::createAtomicUpdate(
4342  const LocationDescription &Loc, InsertPointTy AllocaIP, AtomicOpValue &X,
4343  Value *Expr, AtomicOrdering AO, AtomicRMWInst::BinOp RMWOp,
4344  AtomicUpdateCallbackTy &UpdateOp, bool IsXBinopExpr) {
4345  assert(!isConflictIP(Loc.IP, AllocaIP) && "IPs must not be ambiguous");
4346  if (!updateToLocation(Loc))
4347  return Loc.IP;
4348 
4349  LLVM_DEBUG({
4350  Type *XTy = X.Var->getType();
4351  assert(XTy->isPointerTy() &&
4352  "OMP Atomic expects a pointer to target memory");
4353  Type *XElemTy = X.ElemTy;
4354  assert((XElemTy->isFloatingPointTy() || XElemTy->isIntegerTy() ||
4355  XElemTy->isPointerTy()) &&
4356  "OMP atomic update expected a scalar type");
4357  assert((RMWOp != AtomicRMWInst::Max) && (RMWOp != AtomicRMWInst::Min) &&
4358  (RMWOp != AtomicRMWInst::UMax) && (RMWOp != AtomicRMWInst::UMin) &&
4359  "OpenMP atomic does not support LT or GT operations");
4360  });
4361 
4362  emitAtomicUpdate(AllocaIP, X.Var, X.ElemTy, Expr, AO, RMWOp, UpdateOp,
4363  X.IsVolatile, IsXBinopExpr);
4364  checkAndEmitFlushAfterAtomic(Loc, AO, AtomicKind::Update);
4365  return Builder.saveIP();
4366 }
4367 
4368 // FIXME: Duplicating AtomicExpand
4369 Value *OpenMPIRBuilder::emitRMWOpAsInstruction(Value *Src1, Value *Src2,
4370  AtomicRMWInst::BinOp RMWOp) {
4371  switch (RMWOp) {
4372  case AtomicRMWInst::Add:
4373  return Builder.CreateAdd(Src1, Src2);
4374  case AtomicRMWInst::Sub:
4375  return Builder.CreateSub(Src1, Src2);
4376  case AtomicRMWInst::And:
4377  return Builder.CreateAnd(Src1, Src2);
4378  case AtomicRMWInst::Nand:
4379  return Builder.CreateNeg(Builder.CreateAnd(Src1, Src2));
4380  case AtomicRMWInst::Or:
4381  return Builder.CreateOr(Src1, Src2);
4382  case AtomicRMWInst::Xor:
4383  return Builder.CreateXor(Src1, Src2);
4384  case AtomicRMWInst::Xchg:
4385  case AtomicRMWInst::FAdd:
4386  case AtomicRMWInst::FSub:
4387  case AtomicRMWInst::BAD_BINOP:
4388  case AtomicRMWInst::Max:
4389  case AtomicRMWInst::Min:
4390  case AtomicRMWInst::UMax:
4391  case AtomicRMWInst::UMin:
4392  case AtomicRMWInst::FMax:
4393  case AtomicRMWInst::FMin:
4394  case AtomicRMWInst::UIncWrap:
4395  case AtomicRMWInst::UDecWrap:
4396  llvm_unreachable("Unsupported atomic update operation");
4397  }
4398  llvm_unreachable("Unsupported atomic update operation");
4399 }
4400 
4401 std::pair<Value *, Value *> OpenMPIRBuilder::emitAtomicUpdate(
4402  InsertPointTy AllocaIP, Value *X, Type *XElemTy, Value *Expr,
4403  AtomicOrdering AO, AtomicRMWInst::BinOp RMWOp,
4404  AtomicUpdateCallbackTy &UpdateOp, bool VolatileX, bool IsXBinopExpr) {
4405  // TODO: handle the case where XElemTy is not byte-sized or not a power of 2
4406  // or a complex datatype.
4407  bool emitRMWOp = false;
4408  switch (RMWOp) {
4409  case AtomicRMWInst::Add:
4410  case AtomicRMWInst::And:
4411  case AtomicRMWInst::Nand:
4412  case AtomicRMWInst::Or:
4413  case AtomicRMWInst::Xor:
4414  case AtomicRMWInst::Xchg:
4415  emitRMWOp = XElemTy;
4416  break;
4417  case AtomicRMWInst::Sub:
4418  emitRMWOp = (IsXBinopExpr && XElemTy);
4419  break;
4420  default:
4421  emitRMWOp = false;
4422  }
4423  emitRMWOp &= XElemTy->isIntegerTy();
4424 
4425  std::pair<Value *, Value *> Res;
4426  if (emitRMWOp) {
4427  Res.first = Builder.CreateAtomicRMW(RMWOp, X, Expr, llvm::MaybeAlign(), AO);
4428  // not needed except in case of postfix captures. Generate anyway for
4429  // consistency with the else part. Will be removed with any DCE pass.
4430  // AtomicRMWInst::Xchg does not have a coressponding instruction.
4431  if (RMWOp == AtomicRMWInst::Xchg)
4432  Res.second = Res.first;
4433  else
4434  Res.second = emitRMWOpAsInstruction(Res.first, Expr, RMWOp);
4435  } else {
4436  unsigned Addrspace = cast<PointerType>(X->getType())->getAddressSpace();
4437  IntegerType *IntCastTy =
4438  IntegerType::get(M.getContext(), XElemTy->getScalarSizeInBits());
4439  Value *XBCast =
4440  Builder.CreateBitCast(X, IntCastTy->getPointerTo(Addrspace));
4441  LoadInst *OldVal =
4442  Builder.CreateLoad(IntCastTy, XBCast, X->getName() + ".atomic.load");
4443  OldVal->setAtomic(AO);
4444  // CurBB
4445  // | /---\
4446  // ContBB |
4447  // | \---/
4448  // ExitBB
4449  BasicBlock *CurBB = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
4450  Instruction *CurBBTI = CurBB->getTerminator();
4451  CurBBTI = CurBBTI ? CurBBTI : Builder.CreateUnreachable();
4452  BasicBlock *ExitBB =
4453  CurBB->splitBasicBlock(CurBBTI, X->getName() + ".atomic.exit");
4454  BasicBlock *ContBB = CurBB->splitBasicBlock(CurBB->getTerminator(),
4455  X->getName() + ".atomic.cont");
4456  ContBB->getTerminator()->eraseFromParent();
4457  Builder.restoreIP(AllocaIP);
4458  AllocaInst *NewAtomicAddr = Builder.CreateAlloca(XElemTy);
4459  NewAtomicAddr->setName(X->getName() + "x.new.val");
4460  Builder.SetInsertPoint(ContBB);
4461  llvm::PHINode *PHI = Builder.CreatePHI(OldVal->getType(), 2);
4462  PHI->addIncoming(OldVal, CurBB);
4463  IntegerType *NewAtomicCastTy =
4464  IntegerType::get(M.getContext(), XElemTy->getScalarSizeInBits());
4465  bool IsIntTy = XElemTy->isIntegerTy();
4466  Value *NewAtomicIntAddr =
4467  (IsIntTy)
4468  ? NewAtomicAddr
4469  : Builder.CreateBitCast(NewAtomicAddr,
4470  NewAtomicCastTy->getPointerTo(Addrspace));
4471  Value *OldExprVal = PHI;
4472  if (!IsIntTy) {
4473  if (XElemTy->isFloatingPointTy()) {
4474  OldExprVal = Builder.CreateBitCast(PHI, XElemTy,
4475  X->getName() + ".atomic.fltCast");
4476  } else {
4477  OldExprVal = Builder.CreateIntToPtr(PHI, XElemTy,
4478  X->getName() + ".atomic.ptrCast");
4479  }
4480  }
4481 
4482  Value *Upd = UpdateOp(OldExprVal, Builder);
4483  Builder.CreateStore(Upd, NewAtomicAddr);
4484  LoadInst *DesiredVal = Builder.CreateLoad(IntCastTy, NewAtomicIntAddr);
4485  Value *XAddr =
4486  (IsIntTy)
4487  ? X
4488  : Builder.CreateBitCast(X, IntCastTy->getPointerTo(Addrspace));
4489  AtomicOrdering Failure =
4490  llvm::AtomicCmpXchgInst::getStrongestFailureOrdering(AO);
4491  AtomicCmpXchgInst *Result = Builder.CreateAtomicCmpXchg(
4492  XAddr, PHI, DesiredVal, llvm::MaybeAlign(), AO, Failure);
4493  Result->setVolatile(VolatileX);
4494  Value *PreviousVal = Builder.CreateExtractValue(Result, /*Idxs=*/0);
4495  Value *SuccessFailureVal = Builder.CreateExtractValue(Result, /*Idxs=*/1);
4496  PHI->addIncoming(PreviousVal, Builder.GetInsertBlock());
4497  Builder.CreateCondBr(SuccessFailureVal, ExitBB, ContBB);
4498 
4499  Res.first = OldExprVal;
4500  Res.second = Upd;
4501 
4502  // set Insertion point in exit block
4503  if (UnreachableInst *ExitTI =
4504  dyn_cast<UnreachableInst>(ExitBB->getTerminator())) {
4505  CurBBTI->eraseFromParent();
4506  Builder.SetInsertPoint(ExitBB);
4507  } else {
4508  Builder.SetInsertPoint(ExitTI);
4509  }
4510  }
4511 
4512  return Res;
4513 }
4514 
4515 OpenMPIRBuilder::InsertPointTy OpenMPIRBuilder::createAtomicCapture(
4516  const LocationDescription &Loc, InsertPointTy AllocaIP, AtomicOpValue &X,
4517  AtomicOpValue &V, Value *Expr, AtomicOrdering AO,
4518  AtomicRMWInst::BinOp RMWOp, AtomicUpdateCallbackTy &UpdateOp,
4519  bool UpdateExpr, bool IsPostfixUpdate, bool IsXBinopExpr) {
4520  if (!updateToLocation(Loc))
4521  return Loc.IP;
4522 
4523  LLVM_DEBUG({
4524  Type *XTy = X.Var->getType();
4525  assert(XTy->isPointerTy() &&
4526  "OMP Atomic expects a pointer to target memory");
4527  Type *XElemTy = X.ElemTy;
4528  assert((XElemTy->isFloatingPointTy() || XElemTy->isIntegerTy() ||
4529  XElemTy->isPointerTy()) &&
4530  "OMP atomic capture expected a scalar type");
4531  assert((RMWOp != AtomicRMWInst::Max) && (RMWOp != AtomicRMWInst::Min) &&
4532  "OpenMP atomic does not support LT or GT operations");
4533  });
4534 
4535  // If UpdateExpr is 'x' updated with some `expr` not based on 'x',
4536  // 'x' is simply atomically rewritten with 'expr'.
4537  AtomicRMWInst::BinOp AtomicOp = (UpdateExpr ? RMWOp : AtomicRMWInst::Xchg);
4538  std::pair<Value *, Value *> Result =
4539  emitAtomicUpdate(AllocaIP, X.Var, X.ElemTy, Expr, AO, AtomicOp, UpdateOp,
4540  X.IsVolatile, IsXBinopExpr);
4541 
4542  Value *CapturedVal = (IsPostfixUpdate ? Result.first : Result.second);
4543  Builder.CreateStore(CapturedVal, V.Var, V.IsVolatile);
4544 
4545  checkAndEmitFlushAfterAtomic(Loc, AO, AtomicKind::Capture);
4546  return Builder.saveIP();
4547 }
4548 
4549 OpenMPIRBuilder::InsertPointTy OpenMPIRBuilder::createAtomicCompare(
4550  const LocationDescription &Loc, AtomicOpValue &X, AtomicOpValue &V,
4551  AtomicOpValue &R, Value *E, Value *D, AtomicOrdering AO,
4552  omp::OMPAtomicCompareOp Op, bool IsXBinopExpr, bool IsPostfixUpdate,
4553  bool IsFailOnly) {
4554 
4555  if (!updateToLocation(Loc))
4556  return Loc.IP;
4557 
4558  assert(X.Var->getType()->isPointerTy() &&
4559  "OMP atomic expects a pointer to target memory");
4560  // compare capture
4561  if (V.Var) {
4562  assert(V.Var->getType()->isPointerTy() && "v.var must be of pointer type");
4563  assert(V.ElemTy == X.ElemTy && "x and v must be of same type");
4564  }
4565 
4566  bool IsInteger = E->getType()->isIntegerTy();
4567 
4568  if (Op == OMPAtomicCompareOp::EQ) {
4569  AtomicOrdering Failure = AtomicCmpXchgInst::getStrongestFailureOrdering(AO);
4570  AtomicCmpXchgInst *Result = nullptr;
4571  if (!IsInteger) {
4572  unsigned Addrspace =
4573  cast<PointerType>(X.Var->getType())->getAddressSpace();
4574  IntegerType *IntCastTy =
4575  IntegerType::get(M.getContext(), X.ElemTy->getScalarSizeInBits());
4576  Value *XBCast =
4577  Builder.CreateBitCast(X.Var, IntCastTy->getPointerTo(Addrspace));
4578  Value *EBCast = Builder.CreateBitCast(E, IntCastTy);
4579  Value *DBCast = Builder.CreateBitCast(D, IntCastTy);
4580  Result = Builder.CreateAtomicCmpXchg(XBCast, EBCast, DBCast, MaybeAlign(),
4581  AO, Failure);
4582  } else {
4583  Result =
4584  Builder.CreateAtomicCmpXchg(X.Var, E, D, MaybeAlign(), AO, Failure);
4585  }
4586 
4587  if (V.Var) {
4588  Value *OldValue = Builder.CreateExtractValue(Result, /*Idxs=*/0);
4589  if (!IsInteger)
4590  OldValue = Builder.CreateBitCast(OldValue, X.ElemTy);
4591  assert(OldValue->getType() == V.ElemTy &&
4592  "OldValue and V must be of same type");
4593  if (IsPostfixUpdate) {
4594  Builder.CreateStore(OldValue, V.Var, V.IsVolatile);
4595  } else {
4596  Value *SuccessOrFail = Builder.CreateExtractValue(Result, /*Idxs=*/1);
4597  if (IsFailOnly) {
4598  // CurBB----
4599  // | |
4600  // v |
4601  // ContBB |
4602  // | |
4603  // v |
4604  // ExitBB <-
4605  //
4606  // where ContBB only contains the store of old value to 'v'.
4607  BasicBlock *CurBB = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
4608  Instruction *CurBBTI = CurBB->getTerminator();
4609  CurBBTI = CurBBTI ? CurBBTI : Builder.CreateUnreachable();
4610  BasicBlock *ExitBB = CurBB->splitBasicBlock(
4611  CurBBTI, X.Var->getName() + ".atomic.exit");
4612  BasicBlock *ContBB = CurBB->splitBasicBlock(
4613  CurBB->getTerminator(), X.Var->getName() + ".atomic.cont");
4614  ContBB->getTerminator()->eraseFromParent();
4615  CurBB->getTerminator()->eraseFromParent();
4616 
4617  Builder.CreateCondBr(SuccessOrFail, ExitBB, ContBB);
4618 
4619  Builder.SetInsertPoint(ContBB);
4620  Builder.CreateStore(OldValue, V.Var);
4621  Builder.CreateBr(ExitBB);
4622 
4623  if (UnreachableInst *ExitTI =
4624  dyn_cast<UnreachableInst>(ExitBB->getTerminator())) {
4625  CurBBTI->eraseFromParent();
4626  Builder.SetInsertPoint(ExitBB);
4627  } else {
4628  Builder.SetInsertPoint(ExitTI);
4629  }
4630  } else {
4631  Value *CapturedValue =
4632  Builder.CreateSelect(SuccessOrFail, E, OldValue);
4633  Builder.CreateStore(CapturedValue, V.Var, V.IsVolatile);
4634  }
4635  }
4636  }
4637  // The comparison result has to be stored.
4638  if (R.Var) {
4639  assert(R.Var->getType()->isPointerTy() &&
4640  "r.var must be of pointer type");
4641  assert(R.ElemTy->isIntegerTy() && "r must be of integral type");
4642 
4643  Value *SuccessFailureVal = Builder.CreateExtractValue(Result, /*Idxs=*/1);
4644  Value *ResultCast = R.IsSigned
4645  ? Builder.CreateSExt(SuccessFailureVal, R.ElemTy)
4646  : Builder.CreateZExt(SuccessFailureVal, R.ElemTy);
4647  Builder.CreateStore(ResultCast, R.Var, R.IsVolatile);
4648  }
4649  } else {
4650  assert((Op == OMPAtomicCompareOp::MAX || Op == OMPAtomicCompareOp::MIN) &&
4651  "Op should be either max or min at this point");
4652  assert(!IsFailOnly && "IsFailOnly is only valid when the comparison is ==");
4653 
4654  // Reverse the ordop as the OpenMP forms are different from LLVM forms.
4655  // Let's take max as example.
4656  // OpenMP form:
4657  // x = x > expr ? expr : x;
4658  // LLVM form:
4659  // *ptr = *ptr > val ? *ptr : val;
4660  // We need to transform to LLVM form.
4661  // x = x <= expr ? x : expr;
4662  AtomicRMWInst::BinOp NewOp;
4663  if (IsXBinopExpr) {
4664  if (IsInteger) {
4665  if (X.IsSigned)
4666  NewOp = Op == OMPAtomicCompareOp::MAX ? AtomicRMWInst::Min
4667  : AtomicRMWInst::Max;
4668  else
4669  NewOp = Op == OMPAtomicCompareOp::MAX ? AtomicRMWInst::UMin
4670  : AtomicRMWInst::UMax;
4671  } else {
4672  NewOp = Op == OMPAtomicCompareOp::MAX ? AtomicRMWInst::FMin
4673  : AtomicRMWInst::FMax;
4674  }
4675  } else {
4676  if (IsInteger) {
4677  if (X.IsSigned)
4678  NewOp = Op == OMPAtomicCompareOp::MAX ? AtomicRMWInst::Max
4679  : AtomicRMWInst::Min;
4680  else
4681  NewOp = Op == OMPAtomicCompareOp::MAX ? AtomicRMWInst::UMax
4682  : AtomicRMWInst::UMin;
4683  } else {
4684  NewOp = Op == OMPAtomicCompareOp::MAX ? AtomicRMWInst::FMax
4685  : AtomicRMWInst::FMin;
4686  }
4687  }
4688 
4689  AtomicRMWInst *OldValue =
4690  Builder.CreateAtomicRMW(NewOp, X.Var, E, MaybeAlign(), AO);
4691  if (V.Var) {
4692  Value *CapturedValue = nullptr;
4693  if (IsPostfixUpdate) {
4694  CapturedValue = OldValue;
4695  } else {
4696  CmpInst::Predicate Pred;
4697  switch (NewOp) {
4698  case AtomicRMWInst::Max:
4699  Pred = CmpInst::ICMP_SGT;
4700  break;
4701  case AtomicRMWInst::UMax:
4702  Pred = CmpInst::ICMP_UGT;
4703  break;
4704  case AtomicRMWInst::FMax:
4705  Pred = CmpInst::FCMP_OGT;
4706  break;
4707  case AtomicRMWInst::Min:
4708  Pred = CmpInst::ICMP_SLT;
4709  break;
4710  case AtomicRMWInst::UMin:
4711  Pred = CmpInst::ICMP_ULT;
4712  break;
4713  case AtomicRMWInst::FMin:
4714  Pred = CmpInst::FCMP_OLT;
4715  break;
4716  default:
4717  llvm_unreachable("unexpected comparison op");
4718  }
4719  Value *NonAtomicCmp = Builder.CreateCmp(Pred, OldValue, E);
4720  CapturedValue = Builder.CreateSelect(NonAtomicCmp, E, OldValue);
4721  }
4722  Builder.CreateStore(CapturedValue, V.Var, V.IsVolatile);
4723  }
4724  }
4725 
4726  checkAndEmitFlushAfterAtomic(Loc, AO, AtomicKind::Compare);
4727 
4728  return Builder.saveIP();
4729 }

4731 GlobalVariable *
4732 OpenMPIRBuilder::createOffloadMapnames(SmallVectorImpl<llvm::Constant *> &Names,
4733  std::string VarName) {
4734  llvm::Constant *MapNamesArrayInit = llvm::ConstantArray::get(
4735  llvm::ArrayType::get(
4736  llvm::Type::getInt8Ty(M.getContext())->getPointerTo(), Names.size()),
4737  Names);
4738  auto *MapNamesArrayGlobal = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
4739  M, MapNamesArrayInit->getType(),
4740  /*isConstant=*/true, llvm::GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage, MapNamesArrayInit,
4741  VarName);
4742  return MapNamesArrayGlobal;
4743 }

4745 // Create all simple and struct types exposed by the runtime and remember
4746 // the llvm::PointerTypes of them for easy access later.
4747 void OpenMPIRBuilder::initializeTypes(Module &M) {
4748  LLVMContext &Ctx = M.getContext();
4749  StructType *T;
4750 #define OMP_TYPE(VarName, InitValue) VarName = InitValue;
4751 #define OMP_ARRAY_TYPE(VarName, ElemTy, ArraySize) \
4752  VarName##Ty = ArrayType::get(ElemTy, ArraySize); \
4753  VarName##PtrTy = PointerType::getUnqual(VarName##Ty);
4754 #define OMP_FUNCTION_TYPE(VarName, IsVarArg, ReturnType, ...) \
4755  VarName = FunctionType::get(ReturnType, {__VA_ARGS__}, IsVarArg); \
4756  VarName##Ptr = PointerType::getUnqual(VarName);
4757 #define OMP_STRUCT_TYPE(VarName, StructName, Packed, ...) \
4758  T = StructType::getTypeByName(Ctx, StructName); \
4759  if (!T) \
4760  T = StructType::create(Ctx, {__VA_ARGS__}, StructName, Packed); \
4761  VarName = T; \
4762  VarName##Ptr = PointerType::getUnqual(T);
4763 #include "llvm/Frontend/OpenMP/OMPKinds.def"
4764 }
4765 
4766 void OpenMPIRBuilder::OutlineInfo::collectBlocks(
4767  SmallPtrSetImpl<BasicBlock *> &BlockSet,
4768  SmallVectorImpl<BasicBlock *> &BlockVector) {
4769  SmallVector<BasicBlock *, 32> Worklist;
4770  BlockSet.insert(EntryBB);
4771  BlockSet.insert(ExitBB);
4772 
4773  Worklist.push_back(EntryBB);
4774  while (!Worklist.empty()) {
4775  BasicBlock *BB = Worklist.pop_back_val();
4776  BlockVector.push_back(BB);
4777  for (BasicBlock *SuccBB : successors(BB))
4778  if (BlockSet.insert(SuccBB).second)
4779  Worklist.push_back(SuccBB);
4780  }
4781 }
4782 
4783 void OpenMPIRBuilder::createOffloadEntry(Constant *ID, Constant *Addr,
4784  uint64_t Size, int32_t Flags,
4785  GlobalValue::LinkageTypes) {
4786  if (!Config.isTargetCodegen()) {
4787  emitOffloadingEntry(ID, Addr->getName(), Size, Flags);
4788  return;
4789  }
4790  // TODO: Add support for global variables on the device after declare target
4791  // support.
4792  Function *Fn = dyn_cast<Function>(Addr);
4793  if (!Fn)
4794  return;
4795 
4796  Module &M = *(Fn->getParent());
4797  LLVMContext &Ctx = M.getContext();
4798 
4799  // Get "nvvm.annotations" metadata node.
4800  NamedMDNode *MD = M.getOrInsertNamedMetadata("nvvm.annotations");
4801 
4802  Metadata *MDVals[] = {
4803  ConstantAsMetadata::get(Fn), MDString::get(Ctx, "kernel"),
4804  ConstantAsMetadata::get(ConstantInt::get(Type::getInt32Ty(Ctx), 1))};
4805  // Append metadata to nvvm.annotations.
4806  MD->addOperand(MDNode::get(Ctx, MDVals));
4807 
4808  // Add a function attribute for the kernel.
4809  Fn->addFnAttr(Attribute::get(Ctx, "kernel"));
4810 }
4811 
4812 // We only generate metadata for function that contain target regions.
4813 void OpenMPIRBuilder::createOffloadEntriesAndInfoMetadata(
4814  OffloadEntriesInfoManager &OffloadEntriesInfoManager,
4815  EmitMetadataErrorReportFunctionTy &ErrorFn) {
4816 
4817  // If there are no entries, we don't need to do anything.
4818  if (OffloadEntriesInfoManager.empty())
4819  return;
4820 
4821  LLVMContext &C = M.getContext();
4822  SmallVector<std::pair<const OffloadEntriesInfoManager::OffloadEntryInfo *,
4823  TargetRegionEntryInfo>,
4824  16>
4825  OrderedEntries(OffloadEntriesInfoManager.size());
4826 
4827  // Auxiliary methods to create metadata values and strings.
4828  auto &&GetMDInt = [this](unsigned V) {
4829  return ConstantAsMetadata::get(ConstantInt::get(Builder.getInt32Ty(), V));
4830  };
4831 
4832  auto &&GetMDString = [&C](StringRef V) { return MDString::get(C, V); };
4833 
4834  // Create the offloading info metadata node.
4835  NamedMDNode *MD = M.getOrInsertNamedMetadata("omp_offload.info");
4836  auto &&TargetRegionMetadataEmitter =
4837  [&C, MD, &OrderedEntries, &GetMDInt, &GetMDString](
4838  const TargetRegionEntryInfo &EntryInfo,
4839  const OffloadEntriesInfoManager::OffloadEntryInfoTargetRegion &E) {
4840  // Generate metadata for target regions. Each entry of this metadata
4841  // contains:
4842  // - Entry 0 -> Kind of this type of metadata (0).
4843  // - Entry 1 -> Device ID of the file where the entry was identified.
4844  // - Entry 2 -> File ID of the file where the entry was identified.
4845  // - Entry 3 -> Mangled name of the function where the entry was
4846  // identified.
4847  // - Entry 4 -> Line in the file where the entry was identified.
4848  // - Entry 5 -> Count of regions at this DeviceID/FilesID/Line.
4849  // - Entry 6 -> Order the entry was created.
4850  // The first element of the metadata node is the kind.
4851  Metadata *Ops[] = {
4852  GetMDInt(E.getKind()), GetMDInt(EntryInfo.DeviceID),
4853  GetMDInt(EntryInfo.FileID), GetMDString(EntryInfo.ParentName),
4854  GetMDInt(EntryInfo.Line), GetMDInt(EntryInfo.Count),
4855  GetMDInt(E.getOrder())};
4856 
4857  // Save this entry in the right position of the ordered entries array.
4858  OrderedEntries[E.getOrder()] = std::make_pair(&E, EntryInfo);
4859 
4860  // Add metadata to the named metadata node.
4861  MD->addOperand(MDNode::get(C, Ops));
4862  };
4863 
4864  OffloadEntriesInfoManager.actOnTargetRegionEntriesInfo(
4865  TargetRegionMetadataEmitter);
4866 
4867  // Create function that emits metadata for each device global variable entry;
4868  auto &&DeviceGlobalVarMetadataEmitter =
4869  [&C, &OrderedEntries, &GetMDInt, &GetMDString, MD](
4870  StringRef MangledName,
4871  const OffloadEntriesInfoManager::OffloadEntryInfoDeviceGlobalVar &E) {
4872  // Generate metadata for global variables. Each entry of this metadata
4873  // contains:
4874  // - Entry 0 -> Kind of this type of metadata (1).
4875  // - Entry 1 -> Mangled name of the variable.
4876  // - Entry 2 -> Declare target kind.
4877  // - Entry 3 -> Order the entry was created.
4878  // The first element of the metadata node is the kind.
4879  Metadata *Ops[] = {GetMDInt(E.getKind()), GetMDString(MangledName),
4880  GetMDInt(E.getFlags()), GetMDInt(E.getOrder())};
4881 
4882  // Save this entry in the right position of the ordered entries array.
4883  TargetRegionEntryInfo varInfo(MangledName, 0, 0, 0);
4884  OrderedEntries[E.getOrder()] = std::make_pair(&E, varInfo);
4885 
4886  // Add metadata to the named metadata node.
4887  MD->addOperand(MDNode::get(C, Ops));
4888  };
4889 
4890  OffloadEntriesInfoManager.actOnDeviceGlobalVarEntriesInfo(
4891  DeviceGlobalVarMetadataEmitter);
4892 
4893  for (const auto &E : OrderedEntries) {
4894  assert(E.first && "All ordered entries must exist!");
4895  if (const auto *CE =
4896  dyn_cast<OffloadEntriesInfoManager::OffloadEntryInfoTargetRegion>(
4897  E.first)) {
4898  if (!CE->getID() || !CE->getAddress()) {
4899  // Do not blame the entry if the parent funtion is not emitted.
4900  TargetRegionEntryInfo EntryInfo = E.second;
4901  StringRef FnName = EntryInfo.ParentName;
4902  if (!M.getNamedValue(FnName))
4903  continue;
4904  ErrorFn(EMIT_MD_TARGET_REGION_ERROR, EntryInfo);
4905  continue;
4906  }
4907  createOffloadEntry(CE->getID(), CE->getAddress(),
4908  /*Size=*/0, CE->getFlags(),
4909  GlobalValue::WeakAnyLinkage);
4910  } else if (const auto *CE = dyn_cast<
4911  OffloadEntriesInfoManager::OffloadEntryInfoDeviceGlobalVar>(
4912  E.first)) {
4913  OffloadEntriesInfoManager::OMPTargetGlobalVarEntryKind Flags =
4914  static_cast<OffloadEntriesInfoManager::OMPTargetGlobalVarEntryKind>(
4915  CE->getFlags());
4916  switch (Flags) {
4917  case OffloadEntriesInfoManager::OMPTargetGlobalVarEntryTo: {
4918  if (Config.isEmbedded() && Config.hasRequiresUnifiedSharedMemory())
4919  continue;
4920  if (!CE->getAddress()) {
4921  ErrorFn(EMIT_MD_DECLARE_TARGET_ERROR, E.second);
4922  continue;
4923  }
4924  // The vaiable has no definition - no need to add the entry.
4925  if (CE->getVarSize() == 0)
4926  continue;
4927  break;
4928  }
4929  case OffloadEntriesInfoManager::OMPTargetGlobalVarEntryLink:
4930  assert(((Config.isEmbedded() && !CE->getAddress()) ||
4931  (!Config.isEmbedded() && CE->getAddress())) &&
4932  "Declaret target link address is set.");
4933  if (Config.isEmbedded())
4934  continue;
4935  if (!CE->getAddress()) {
4936  ErrorFn(EMIT_MD_GLOBAL_VAR_LINK_ERROR, TargetRegionEntryInfo());
4937  continue;
4938  }
4939  break;
4940  }
4941 
4942  // Hidden or internal symbols on the device are not externally visible.
4943  // We should not attempt to register them by creating an offloading
4944  // entry.
4945  if (auto *GV = dyn_cast<GlobalValue>(CE->getAddress()))
4946  if (GV->hasLocalLinkage() || GV->hasHiddenVisibility())
4947  continue;
4948 
4949  createOffloadEntry(CE->getAddress(), CE->getAddress(), CE->getVarSize(),
4950  Flags, CE->getLinkage());
4951 
4952  } else {
4953  llvm_unreachable("Unsupported entry kind.");
4954  }
4955  }
4956 }
4957 
4958 void TargetRegionEntryInfo::getTargetRegionEntryFnName(
4959  SmallVectorImpl<char> &Name, StringRef ParentName, unsigned DeviceID,
4960  unsigned FileID, unsigned Line, unsigned Count) {
4961  raw_svector_ostream OS(Name);
4962  OS << "__omp_offloading" << llvm::format("_%x", DeviceID)
4963  << llvm::format("_%x_", FileID) << ParentName << "_l" << Line;
4964  if (Count)
4965  OS << "_" << Count;
4966 }

4976 /// Loads all the offload entries information from the host IR
4977 /// metadata.
4978 void OpenMPIRBuilder::loadOffloadInfoMetadata(
4979  Module &M, OffloadEntriesInfoManager &OffloadEntriesInfoManager) {
4980  // If we are in target mode, load the metadata from the host IR. This code has
4981  // to match the metadata creation in createOffloadEntriesAndInfoMetadata().
4982 
4983  NamedMDNode *MD = M.getNamedMetadata(ompOffloadInfoName);
4984  if (!MD)
4985  return;
4986 
4987  for (MDNode *MN : MD->operands()) {
4988  auto &&GetMDInt = [MN](unsigned Idx) {
4989  auto *V = cast<ConstantAsMetadata>(MN->getOperand(Idx));
4990  return cast<ConstantInt>(V->getValue())->getZExtValue();
4991  };
4992 
4993  auto &&GetMDString = [MN](unsigned Idx) {
4994  auto *V = cast<MDString>(MN->getOperand(Idx));
4995  return V->getString();
4996  };
4997 
4998  switch (GetMDInt(0)) {
4999  default:
5000  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected metadata!");
5001  break;
5002  case OffloadEntriesInfoManager::OffloadEntryInfo::
5003  OffloadingEntryInfoTargetRegion: {
5004  TargetRegionEntryInfo EntryInfo(/*ParentName=*/GetMDString(3),
5005  /*DeviceID=*/GetMDInt(1),
5006  /*FileID=*/GetMDInt(2),
5007  /*Line=*/GetMDInt(4),
5008  /*Count=*/GetMDInt(5));
5009  OffloadEntriesInfoManager.initializeTargetRegionEntryInfo(
5010  EntryInfo, /*Order=*/GetMDInt(6));
5011  break;
5012  }
5013  case OffloadEntriesInfoManager::OffloadEntryInfo::
5014  OffloadingEntryInfoDeviceGlobalVar:
5015  OffloadEntriesInfoManager.initializeDeviceGlobalVarEntryInfo(
5016  /*MangledName=*/GetMDString(1),
5017  static_cast<OffloadEntriesInfoManager::OMPTargetGlobalVarEntryKind>(
5018  /*Flags=*/GetMDInt(2)),
5019  /*Order=*/GetMDInt(3));
5020  break;
5021  }
5022  }
5023 }
5024 
5025 bool OffloadEntriesInfoManager::empty() const {
5026  return OffloadEntriesTargetRegion.empty() &&
5027  OffloadEntriesDeviceGlobalVar.empty();
5028 }

5030 unsigned OffloadEntriesInfoManager::getTargetRegionEntryInfoCount(
5031  const TargetRegionEntryInfo &EntryInfo) const {
5032  auto It = OffloadEntriesTargetRegionCount.find(
5033  getTargetRegionEntryCountKey(EntryInfo));
5034  if (It == OffloadEntriesTargetRegionCount.end())
5035  return 0;
5036  return It->second;
5037 }
5038 
5039 void OffloadEntriesInfoManager::incrementTargetRegionEntryInfoCount(
5040  const TargetRegionEntryInfo &EntryInfo) {
5041  OffloadEntriesTargetRegionCount[getTargetRegionEntryCountKey(EntryInfo)] =
5042  EntryInfo.Count + 1;
5043 }
5044 
5045 /// Initialize target region entry.
5046 void OffloadEntriesInfoManager::initializeTargetRegionEntryInfo(
5047  const TargetRegionEntryInfo &EntryInfo, unsigned Order) {
5048  OffloadEntriesTargetRegion[EntryInfo] =
5049  OffloadEntryInfoTargetRegion(Order, /*Addr=*/nullptr, /*ID=*/nullptr,
5050  OMPTargetRegionEntryTargetRegion);
5051  ++OffloadingEntriesNum;
5052 }
5053 
5054 void OffloadEntriesInfoManager::registerTargetRegionEntryInfo(
5055  TargetRegionEntryInfo EntryInfo, Constant *Addr, Constant *ID,
5056  OMPTargetRegionEntryKind Flags) {
5057  assert(EntryInfo.Count == 0 && "expected default EntryInfo");
5058 
5059  // Update the EntryInfo with the next available count for this location.
5060  EntryInfo.Count = getTargetRegionEntryInfoCount(EntryInfo);
5061 
5062  // If we are emitting code for a target, the entry is already initialized,
5063  // only has to be registered.
5064  if (Config.isEmbedded()) {
5065  // This could happen if the device compilation is invoked standalone.
5066  if (!hasTargetRegionEntryInfo(EntryInfo)) {
5067  return;
5068  }
5069  auto &Entry = OffloadEntriesTargetRegion[EntryInfo];
5070  Entry.setAddress(Addr);
5071  Entry.setID(ID);
5072  Entry.setFlags(Flags);
5073  } else {
5074  if (Flags == OffloadEntriesInfoManager::OMPTargetRegionEntryTargetRegion &&
5075  hasTargetRegionEntryInfo(EntryInfo, /*IgnoreAddressId*/ true))
5076  return;
5077  assert(!hasTargetRegionEntryInfo(EntryInfo) &&
5078  "Target region entry already registered!");
5079  OffloadEntryInfoTargetRegion Entry(OffloadingEntriesNum, Addr, ID, Flags);
5080  OffloadEntriesTargetRegion[EntryInfo] = Entry;
5081  ++OffloadingEntriesNum;
5082  }
5083  incrementTargetRegionEntryInfoCount(EntryInfo);
5084 }
5085 
5086 bool OffloadEntriesInfoManager::hasTargetRegionEntryInfo(
5087  TargetRegionEntryInfo EntryInfo, bool IgnoreAddressId) const {
5088 
5089  // Update the EntryInfo with the next available count for this location.
5090  EntryInfo.Count = getTargetRegionEntryInfoCount(EntryInfo);
5091 
5092  auto It = OffloadEntriesTargetRegion.find(EntryInfo);
5093  if (It == OffloadEntriesTargetRegion.end()) {
5094  return false;
5095  }
5096  // Fail if this entry is already registered.
5097  if (!IgnoreAddressId && (It->second.getAddress() || It->second.getID()))
5098  return false;
5099  return true;
5100 }
5101 
5102 void OffloadEntriesInfoManager::actOnTargetRegionEntriesInfo(
5103  const OffloadTargetRegionEntryInfoActTy &Action) {
5104  // Scan all target region entries and perform the provided action.
5105  for (const auto &It : OffloadEntriesTargetRegion) {
5106  Action(It.first, It.second);
5107  }
5108 }
