5110 void OffloadEntriesInfoManager::initializeDeviceGlobalVarEntryInfo(
5111  StringRef Name, OMPTargetGlobalVarEntryKind Flags, unsigned Order) {
5112  OffloadEntriesDeviceGlobalVar.try_emplace(Name, Order, Flags);
5113  ++OffloadingEntriesNum;
5114 }
5115 
5116 void OffloadEntriesInfoManager::registerDeviceGlobalVarEntryInfo(
5117  StringRef VarName, Constant *Addr, int64_t VarSize,
5118  OMPTargetGlobalVarEntryKind Flags, GlobalValue::LinkageTypes Linkage) {
5119  if (Config.isEmbedded()) {
5120  // This could happen if the device compilation is invoked standalone.
5121  if (!hasDeviceGlobalVarEntryInfo(VarName))
5122  return;
5123  auto &Entry = OffloadEntriesDeviceGlobalVar[VarName];
5124  if (Entry.getAddress() && hasDeviceGlobalVarEntryInfo(VarName)) {
5125  if (Entry.getVarSize() == 0) {
5126  Entry.setVarSize(VarSize);
5127  Entry.setLinkage(Linkage);
5128  }
5129  return;
5130  }
5131  Entry.setVarSize(VarSize);
5132  Entry.setLinkage(Linkage);
5133  Entry.setAddress(Addr);
5134  } else {
5135  if (hasDeviceGlobalVarEntryInfo(VarName)) {
5136  auto &Entry = OffloadEntriesDeviceGlobalVar[VarName];
5137  assert(Entry.isValid() && Entry.getFlags() == Flags &&
5138  "Entry not initialized!");
5139  if (Entry.getVarSize() == 0) {
5140  Entry.setVarSize(VarSize);
5141  Entry.setLinkage(Linkage);
5142  }
5143  return;
5144  }
5145  OffloadEntriesDeviceGlobalVar.try_emplace(VarName, OffloadingEntriesNum,
5146  Addr, VarSize, Flags, Linkage);
5147  ++OffloadingEntriesNum;
5148  }
5149 }
5150 
5151 void OffloadEntriesInfoManager::actOnDeviceGlobalVarEntriesInfo(
5152  const OffloadDeviceGlobalVarEntryInfoActTy &Action) {
5153  // Scan all target region entries and perform the provided action.
5154  for (const auto &E : OffloadEntriesDeviceGlobalVar)
5155  Action(E.getKey(), E.getValue());
5156 }
5157 
5158 void CanonicalLoopInfo::collectControlBlocks(
5159  SmallVectorImpl<BasicBlock *> &BBs) {
5160  // We only count those BBs as control block for which we do not need to
5161  // reverse the CFG, i.e. not the loop body which can contain arbitrary control
5162  // flow. For consistency, this also means we do not add the Body block, which
5163  // is just the entry to the body code.
5164  BBs.reserve(BBs.size() + 6);
5165  BBs.append({getPreheader(), Header, Cond, Latch, Exit, getAfter()});
5166 }
5167 
5168 BasicBlock *CanonicalLoopInfo::getPreheader() const {
5169  assert(isValid() && "Requires a valid canonical loop");
5170  for (BasicBlock *Pred : predecessors(Header)) {
5171  if (Pred != Latch)
5172  return Pred;
5173  }
5174  llvm_unreachable("Missing preheader");
5175 }
5176 
5177 void CanonicalLoopInfo::setTripCount(Value *TripCount) {
5178  assert(isValid() && "Requires a valid canonical loop");
5179 
5180  Instruction *CmpI = &getCond()->front();
5181  assert(isa<CmpInst>(CmpI) && "First inst must compare IV with TripCount");
5182  CmpI->setOperand(1, TripCount);
5183 
5184 #ifndef NDEBUG
5185  assertOK();
5186 #endif
5187 }
5188 
5189 void CanonicalLoopInfo::mapIndVar(
5190  llvm::function_ref<Value *(Instruction *)> Updater) {
5191  assert(isValid() && "Requires a valid canonical loop");
5192 
5193  Instruction *OldIV = getIndVar();
5194 
5195  // Record all uses excluding those introduced by the updater. Uses by the
5196  // CanonicalLoopInfo itself to keep track of the number of iterations are
5197  // excluded.
5198  SmallVector<Use *> ReplacableUses;
5199  for (Use &U : OldIV->uses()) {
5200  auto *User = dyn_cast<Instruction>(U.getUser());
5201  if (!User)
5202  continue;
5203  if (User->getParent() == getCond())
5204  continue;
5205  if (User->getParent() == getLatch())
5206  continue;
5207  ReplacableUses.push_back(&U);
5208  }
5209 
5210  // Run the updater that may introduce new uses
5211  Value *NewIV = Updater(OldIV);
5212 
5213  // Replace the old uses with the value returned by the updater.
5214  for (Use *U : ReplacableUses)
5215  U->set(NewIV);
5216 
5217 #ifndef NDEBUG
5218  assertOK();
5219 #endif
5220 }
5221 
5222 void CanonicalLoopInfo::assertOK() const {
5223 #ifndef NDEBUG
5224  // No constraints if this object currently does not describe a loop.
5225  if (!isValid())
5226  return;
5227 
5228  BasicBlock *Preheader = getPreheader();
5229  BasicBlock *Body = getBody();
5230  BasicBlock *After = getAfter();
5231 
5232  // Verify standard control-flow we use for OpenMP loops.
5233  assert(Preheader);
5234  assert(isa<BranchInst>(Preheader->getTerminator()) &&
5235  "Preheader must terminate with unconditional branch");
5236  assert(Preheader->getSingleSuccessor() == Header &&
5237  "Preheader must jump to header");
5238 
5239  assert(Header);
5240  assert(isa<BranchInst>(Header->getTerminator()) &&
5241  "Header must terminate with unconditional branch");
5242  assert(Header->getSingleSuccessor() == Cond &&
5243  "Header must jump to exiting block");
5244 
5245  assert(Cond);
5246  assert(Cond->getSinglePredecessor() == Header &&
5247  "Exiting block only reachable from header");
5248 
5249  assert(isa<BranchInst>(Cond->getTerminator()) &&
5250  "Exiting block must terminate with conditional branch");
5251  assert(size(successors(Cond)) == 2 &&
5252  "Exiting block must have two successors");
5253  assert(cast<BranchInst>(Cond->getTerminator())->getSuccessor(0) == Body &&
5254  "Exiting block's first successor jump to the body");
5255  assert(cast<BranchInst>(Cond->getTerminator())->getSuccessor(1) == Exit &&
5256  "Exiting block's second successor must exit the loop");
5257 
5258  assert(Body);
5259  assert(Body->getSinglePredecessor() == Cond &&
5260  "Body only reachable from exiting block");
5261  assert(!isa<PHINode>(Body->front()));
5262 
5263  assert(Latch);
5264  assert(isa<BranchInst>(Latch->getTerminator()) &&
5265  "Latch must terminate with unconditional branch");
5266  assert(Latch->getSingleSuccessor() == Header && "Latch must jump to header");
5267  // TODO: To support simple redirecting of the end of the body code that has
5268  // multiple; introduce another auxiliary basic block like preheader and after.
5269  assert(Latch->getSinglePredecessor() != nullptr);
5270  assert(!isa<PHINode>(Latch->front()));
5271 
5272  assert(Exit);
5273  assert(isa<BranchInst>(Exit->getTerminator()) &&
5274  "Exit block must terminate with unconditional branch");
5275  assert(Exit->getSingleSuccessor() == After &&
5276  "Exit block must jump to after block");
5277 
5278  assert(After);
5279  assert(After->getSinglePredecessor() == Exit &&
5280  "After block only reachable from exit block");
5281  assert(After->empty() || !isa<PHINode>(After->front()));
5282 
5283  Instruction *IndVar = getIndVar();
5284  assert(IndVar && "Canonical induction variable not found?");
5285  assert(isa<IntegerType>(IndVar->getType()) &&
5286  "Induction variable must be an integer");
5287  assert(cast<PHINode>(IndVar)->getParent() == Header &&
5288  "Induction variable must be a PHI in the loop header");
5289  assert(cast<PHINode>(IndVar)->getIncomingBlock(0) == Preheader);
5290  assert(
5291  cast<ConstantInt>(cast<PHINode>(IndVar)->getIncomingValue(0))->isZero());
5292  assert(cast<PHINode>(IndVar)->getIncomingBlock(1) == Latch);
5293 
5294  auto *NextIndVar = cast<PHINode>(IndVar)->getIncomingValue(1);
5295  assert(cast<Instruction>(NextIndVar)->getParent() == Latch);
5296  assert(cast<BinaryOperator>(NextIndVar)->getOpcode() == BinaryOperator::Add);
5297  assert(cast<BinaryOperator>(NextIndVar)->getOperand(0) == IndVar);
5298  assert(cast<ConstantInt>(cast<BinaryOperator>(NextIndVar)->getOperand(1))
5299  ->isOne());
5300 
5301  Value *TripCount = getTripCount();
5302  assert(TripCount && "Loop trip count not found?");
5303  assert(IndVar->getType() == TripCount->getType() &&
5304  "Trip count and induction variable must have the same type");
5305 
5306  auto *CmpI = cast<CmpInst>(&Cond->front());
5307  assert(CmpI->getPredicate() == CmpInst::ICMP_ULT &&
5308  "Exit condition must be a signed less-than comparison");
5309  assert(CmpI->getOperand(0) == IndVar &&
5310  "Exit condition must compare the induction variable");
5311  assert(CmpI->getOperand(1) == TripCount &&
5312  "Exit condition must compare with the trip count");
5313 #endif
5314 }
5315 
5316 void CanonicalLoopInfo::invalidate() {
5317  Header = nullptr;
5318  Cond = nullptr;
5319  Latch = nullptr;
5320  Exit = nullptr;
5321 }
